WEBVTT

00:11.803 --> 00:13.346
RADIO ANNOUNCER:
"W" who?

00:13.388 --> 00:17.350
WURG 94.9, the Urge,

00:17.392 --> 00:19.269
Haddonfield's home for rock.

00:19.310 --> 00:20.770
WILLIE THE KID:
I'm Willie the Kid,

00:20.812 --> 00:22.856
and there's n-n-nothing
you can do about it.

00:22.897 --> 00:25.650
("Midnight Monsters Hop"
by Jack & Jim playing)

00:29.446 --> 00:32.157
* Late one night
when the moon was tall *

00:32.198 --> 00:34.993
* The midnight monsters
had a ball *

00:35.035 --> 00:38.413
* At the county morgue
till the break of day *

00:38.455 --> 00:40.707
* You could hear
those monsters say *

00:40.749 --> 00:42.375
-* Hey, boo *
-* Hey, boo *

00:42.417 --> 00:44.377
-* You're cool *
-* You're cool *

00:44.419 --> 00:47.088
* At the Midnight
Monsters Hop *

00:47.922 --> 00:50.675
* The mummy was
a-frontin' the band *

00:50.717 --> 00:54.262
* On the yakkety sax
the Invisible Man *

00:54.304 --> 00:57.307
* A zombie on the voodoo drum *

00:57.349 --> 01:00.226
* And the guitar man
was a real weird one *

01:00.268 --> 01:01.728
-* They scowl *
-* They scowl *

01:01.770 --> 01:03.480
-* And they howl *
-* And howl *

01:03.521 --> 01:06.566
* At the Midnight
Monsters Hop *

01:06.608 --> 01:08.610
* *

01:23.667 --> 01:25.794
(lively chatter)

01:25.835 --> 01:28.630
* Just before
the break of day *

01:28.672 --> 01:32.509
* The monsters all
are on their way *

01:32.550 --> 01:34.928
* Back to the coffin
in the old graveyard *

01:34.969 --> 01:38.223
* The Headless Horseman
was a-ridin' hard *

01:38.264 --> 01:39.724
-* They're gone *
-* They're gone *

01:39.766 --> 01:41.518
-* Come dawn *
-* Come dawn *

01:41.559 --> 01:43.937
* At the Midnight
Monsters Hop. *

01:43.978 --> 01:45.522
(doorbell rings)

01:46.314 --> 01:48.066
Corey, you're a lifesaver.

01:48.108 --> 01:49.567
Hi.

01:49.609 --> 01:51.152
How've you been? Come on in.

01:51.194 --> 01:53.279
(playing Bach's Toccata
and Fugue in D minor, BWV 565)

01:53.321 --> 01:55.573
MRS. ALLEN:
Roger! Corey's here!

01:55.615 --> 01:57.909
Sorry this is last-minute,
but Andrea got a stomach bug

01:57.951 --> 02:00.120
-and literally just called me.
-Oh, it's okay.

02:00.161 --> 02:01.788
It's Roger's company
Halloween party,

02:01.830 --> 02:04.457
and I could care less, but...
Roger!

02:04.499 --> 02:06.918
Hope he's better at childcare
than he is at yard work.

02:06.960 --> 02:08.128
You know, next spring,

02:08.169 --> 02:09.212
you should consider
some perennials.

02:09.254 --> 02:10.839
Hydrangeas could really

02:10.880 --> 02:12.590
-balance out that dogwood.
-Saving for college?

02:12.632 --> 02:14.384
-Where did you say
you're going? -Oh, I'm applying

02:14.426 --> 02:16.136
to a few different
engineering programs.

02:16.177 --> 02:18.304
Just saving money this year
so I can go next fall.

02:18.346 --> 02:20.682
Jeremy, the sitter's here!

02:25.186 --> 02:27.272
Jeremy!

02:32.193 --> 02:33.695
(screams, chuckles)

02:33.737 --> 02:34.988
Jeremy!

02:35.030 --> 02:37.490
-Ah! You! I'm gonna get you!
-(Jeremy laughing)

02:37.532 --> 02:41.119
I'm gonna get you.
(growls playfully)

02:41.161 --> 02:42.537
(both laughing)

02:42.579 --> 02:44.164
Crash landing! Kaboom!

02:44.205 --> 02:45.373
Oh!

02:45.415 --> 02:46.791
-(chuckles)
-Beep, beep, beep, beep.

02:46.833 --> 02:49.002
Can you show me how to make
a Thunder Bomber?

02:49.044 --> 02:50.503
Number one of all time.

02:50.545 --> 02:52.964
-My dad can do the best.
-No pressure.

02:53.006 --> 02:54.924
Yeah, I'll sure give it
a shot, little dude.

02:54.966 --> 02:56.509
MR. ALLEN: You gonna be good
for Mr. Corey?

02:56.551 --> 02:58.762
-Corey. Could I talk
to you for a sec? -Yeah.

02:58.803 --> 03:00.555
JEREMY:
Here comes the Thunder Bomber!

03:00.597 --> 03:03.016
I'm gonna put the candy
on the porch.

03:03.058 --> 03:05.602
Trick-or-treat kids
can help themselves.

03:05.643 --> 03:07.896
Help yourself
to anything in the fridge.

03:07.937 --> 03:10.315
MR. ALLEN: She made zucchini
bread. It's actually good.

03:10.357 --> 03:12.359
-(chuckling)
-You have my number.

03:12.400 --> 03:13.860
-Okay.
-If there's an emergency,

03:13.902 --> 03:15.653
but we'll just be
right down the street.

03:15.695 --> 03:17.489
-JEREMY: Crash! -(door closes)
-(inhales deeply)

03:17.530 --> 03:19.866
And there is one thing
I need to tell you.

03:19.908 --> 03:22.702
Since last Halloween--
all the events and,

03:22.744 --> 03:26.206
you know, the headlines
of Michael Myers--

03:26.247 --> 03:28.041
Jeremy's been afraid
of the dark.

03:28.083 --> 03:30.460
(whispering): He's been
wetting the bed at night.

03:30.502 --> 03:34.047
And, um, bedtime has been
difficult. (chuckles)

03:34.089 --> 03:35.465
JEREMY:
I can hear you!

03:35.507 --> 03:37.175
Uh, I can read him a story
or something.

03:37.217 --> 03:39.886
-Does he have a favorite book?
-Then once he goes to bed,

03:39.928 --> 03:41.471
he talks in his sleep.

03:41.513 --> 03:42.931
Says he hears voices.

03:42.972 --> 03:44.724
He's just really
sensitive to things

03:44.766 --> 03:46.559
-that give him bad dreams.
-Right. All that just sounds

03:46.601 --> 03:48.436
like normal kid
imagination stuff, right?

03:48.478 --> 03:49.938
-(Jeremy yelling playfully)
-(door opens)

03:49.979 --> 03:53.274
-No TV and no more candy.
-(door closes)

03:54.234 --> 03:57.112
You guys can play
till 8:30, 8:45.

03:57.153 --> 03:59.447
Then he should go to bed.

03:59.489 --> 04:01.282
-Easy money.
-Yes.

04:01.324 --> 04:03.368
JEREMY:
Gonna come play with me or what?

04:03.410 --> 04:05.453
-(chuckling)
-That sounds like a threat.

04:05.495 --> 04:07.247
It's Halloween.

04:07.288 --> 04:09.582
We're gonna have
a good time tonight.

04:09.624 --> 04:11.084
-(crickets chirping)
-(dog barking in distance)

04:11.126 --> 04:13.837
(man screaming on TV)

04:16.464 --> 04:17.757
JEREMY:
Oh.

04:17.799 --> 04:19.217
-Ugh.
-COREY: Look, man, we can

04:19.259 --> 04:21.428
shut it off if you're scared
of monster movies.

04:21.469 --> 04:23.638
No. No. You're scared.

04:23.680 --> 04:26.016
(chuckling): I'm 21 years old.
I don't get scared.

04:26.057 --> 04:28.226
You're scared because you know
Michael Myers is...

04:28.268 --> 04:30.186
(whispers):
still out there.

04:30.228 --> 04:32.564
Boogeyman's gonna get you.

04:32.605 --> 04:34.774
JEREMY:
He's not gonna get me.

04:34.816 --> 04:37.736
Michael Myers kills
babysitters, not kids.

04:40.822 --> 04:42.699
(screaming)

04:44.117 --> 04:45.952
Okay, that's actually
pretty disgusting

04:45.994 --> 04:47.954
and probably not appropriate
for kids.

04:47.996 --> 04:49.622
Why don't we
shut this off, and...

04:49.664 --> 04:51.041
we can play hide-and-seek
before bed.

04:51.082 --> 04:52.625
Your parents are gonna
be home soon and...

04:52.667 --> 04:54.627
I don't want to play
no hide-and-seek.

04:54.669 --> 04:57.005
It's stupid.
I want to watch this movie.

04:57.047 --> 04:59.507
And I don't really feel like
pretending to be best friends

04:59.549 --> 05:01.801
with an ugly-ass
boy babysitter.

05:05.889 --> 05:08.641
Okay, five minutes,
and then you're going to bed.

05:08.683 --> 05:10.977
You suck at babysitting.

05:11.019 --> 05:13.521
I'm not a babysitter.

05:44.636 --> 05:46.888
(clattering)

05:47.889 --> 05:49.307
Jeremy!

05:49.349 --> 05:51.559
Turn that movie off!

05:54.354 --> 05:56.064
Jeremy?

05:58.942 --> 06:01.069
(mutters):
What are you doing?

06:07.492 --> 06:10.036
(door creaks open)

06:10.078 --> 06:11.496
Jeremy?

06:13.081 --> 06:15.125
(crickets chirping)

06:18.586 --> 06:21.089
* *

06:32.559 --> 06:34.310
Jeremy!

06:34.352 --> 06:36.604
(dog barking in distance)

06:37.605 --> 06:39.649
Jeremy?

06:39.691 --> 06:42.193
Come out, come out,
wherever you are.

06:47.282 --> 06:49.034
Boo!

06:51.202 --> 06:54.080
This isn't funny, Jeremy.

06:56.875 --> 06:58.793
-(door bangs shut)
-(grunts)

07:00.295 --> 07:02.088
Jeremy!

07:02.130 --> 07:04.716
-(panting)
-(distant clattering)

07:14.601 --> 07:16.770
(Jeremy screams)

07:16.811 --> 07:19.022
(running footsteps)

07:22.484 --> 07:24.694
Jeremy?

07:27.739 --> 07:29.741
(door bangs shut)

07:33.995 --> 07:36.873
JEREMY:
Help! Corey, help!

07:37.665 --> 07:40.210
(stairs creaking)

07:43.546 --> 07:45.799
(trembling breaths)

08:00.814 --> 08:02.899
(door creaks)

08:12.033 --> 08:14.119
(whispers):
Jeremy?

08:16.079 --> 08:18.123
* *

08:20.542 --> 08:22.627
(whispers):
Jeremy?

08:26.047 --> 08:27.966
Jeremy?

08:30.719 --> 08:32.762
JEREMY:
He's gonna get you!

08:32.804 --> 08:35.265
He's gonna get you
when you least expect it.

08:44.107 --> 08:46.526
-JEREMY: Is it your bedtime,
Corey? -Okay, Jeremy...

08:46.568 --> 08:48.570
JEREMY (mocking): "Come out,
come out, wherever you are."

08:48.611 --> 08:50.572
You got me, buddy.
Okay, let me out.

08:50.613 --> 08:52.032
-JEREMY: Are you scared?
-Okay?

08:52.073 --> 08:53.950
JEREMY (mocking):
"I'm 21. I'm not scared."

08:53.992 --> 08:56.327
Jeremy, let me out. Let me out!

08:58.538 --> 09:00.623
You little shit!
Let me out of here!

09:00.665 --> 09:02.125
JEREMY (chuckling):
Michael Myers.

09:02.167 --> 09:04.210
-Jeremy, it's not funny, okay?
-(Jeremy laughing)

09:04.252 --> 09:06.296
* *

09:08.131 --> 09:10.133
COREY: Hey, you're gonna
get us both in trouble.

09:10.175 --> 09:11.468
(keys jingling)

09:11.509 --> 09:15.805
Let me out! Let me out!
Let me out! Let me out!

09:15.847 --> 09:17.849
You little shit!

09:17.891 --> 09:20.060
-I'm gonna kill you, Jeremy!
-(banging)

09:20.101 --> 09:21.853
-(grunts)
-JEREMY: Boo!

09:22.645 --> 09:24.606
-What was that?
-(Jeremy screams)

09:25.607 --> 09:27.400
(gasps)

09:27.442 --> 09:29.235
MR. ALLEN:
Jeremy!

09:29.277 --> 09:32.322
-Oh, no! Oh, God, no! Please!
-Jeremy!

09:32.364 --> 09:34.783
-Oh, no. Oh, God.
-(whimpers) Jeremy!

09:34.824 --> 09:36.701
Oh, my God! Jeremy!

09:36.743 --> 09:39.204
(Mrs. Allen whimpering,
sobbing)

09:39.245 --> 09:41.331
-MR. ALLEN: Jeremy.
-MRS. ALLEN: Jeremy!

09:42.415 --> 09:44.125
God, please, no!

09:45.627 --> 09:47.754
What have you done?!

09:47.796 --> 09:51.049
(John Carpenter's
"Halloween" theme plays)

10:09.693 --> 10:11.945
* *

10:33.758 --> 10:36.011
* *

10:57.157 --> 10:59.200
* *

11:23.892 --> 11:26.770
(theme fades)

11:26.811 --> 11:28.271
(school bell ringing)

11:28.313 --> 11:31.191
LAURIE: Haddonfield was
a peaceful town.

11:31.232 --> 11:34.778
And then one Halloween night
many years ago,

11:34.819 --> 11:37.405
all of that was lost.

11:39.616 --> 11:42.369
Michael Myers was pure evil.

11:42.410 --> 11:43.495
(sobbing)

11:43.536 --> 11:44.704
He took our dreams

11:44.746 --> 11:46.498
and turned them into nightmares.

11:52.337 --> 11:56.049
As he was locked away
in his prison...

11:57.842 --> 11:59.803
...I disappeared into mine.

11:59.844 --> 12:02.097
(gunshots)

12:07.811 --> 12:10.313
And then, as I predicted,

12:10.355 --> 12:13.191
40 years later, he escaped,

12:13.233 --> 12:15.902
and Haddonfield was once again
forced to confront

12:15.944 --> 12:17.987
this man in a mask.

12:18.863 --> 12:21.991
(muffled, distorted screaming)

12:27.122 --> 12:29.916
His senseless brutality
ravaged my community...

12:29.958 --> 12:31.918
(muffled, distorted whimpering)

12:31.960 --> 12:33.962
...and killed my daughter.

12:34.754 --> 12:36.965
* *

12:37.841 --> 12:40.301
And then he vanished.

12:41.636 --> 12:43.847
Impossible?

12:43.888 --> 12:45.932
Perhaps.

12:47.183 --> 12:49.978
Truth would evolve into legend

12:50.020 --> 12:53.398
as people searched
for motive and meaning,

12:53.440 --> 12:56.526
looking in the shadows
for their boogeyman.

12:56.568 --> 12:58.653
(thunder crashes)

12:58.695 --> 13:00.321
(muffled, distorted sobbing)

13:02.657 --> 13:04.659
It was an accident.

13:05.452 --> 13:07.287
LAURIE:
In the years that followed,

13:07.328 --> 13:10.248
the people of Haddonfield
descended into a plague

13:10.290 --> 13:13.668
of grief, of blame, of paranoia.

13:14.461 --> 13:16.212
OFFICER:
Do you think he's come back?

13:16.254 --> 13:19.049
Michael doesn't use guns.

13:19.966 --> 13:21.718
LAURIE:
The suffering Michael caused

13:21.760 --> 13:24.179
became an infection
passing on to people

13:24.220 --> 13:26.222
who never even
crossed his path.

13:26.264 --> 13:29.809
And as the town
turned in on itself,

13:29.851 --> 13:33.897
I made a promise not to let
fear rule my life anymore.

13:33.938 --> 13:35.523
(birds chirping)

13:35.565 --> 13:36.983
I bought a home.

13:37.025 --> 13:40.487
A place to live
with love and trust.

13:40.528 --> 13:41.905
Not a trap.

13:41.946 --> 13:44.115
Not a place to hide.

13:46.201 --> 13:47.619
Hey.

13:47.660 --> 13:49.287
It has been four years

13:49.329 --> 13:52.040
since I last saw my monster.

13:53.625 --> 13:58.797
So here I am, a survivor
attempting to share my story

13:58.838 --> 14:01.299
and find healing.

14:02.550 --> 14:07.263
Michael Myers was
the personification of evil.

14:11.559 --> 14:13.019
It's theirs.

14:13.061 --> 14:15.271
It's their wedding rings.

14:17.982 --> 14:20.652
It's up to each of us

14:20.694 --> 14:22.862
whether or not we lock the door

14:22.904 --> 14:25.115
and find our resolve...

14:26.282 --> 14:28.535
...or let him inside.

14:37.836 --> 14:41.423
Let it inside.

14:47.595 --> 14:50.515
Let evil...

14:50.557 --> 14:52.267
inside.

14:54.019 --> 14:56.813
-(wind whistling)
-(alarm beeping)

14:56.855 --> 14:58.898
Allyson! Darn it!

14:59.691 --> 15:01.651
-Honey, I'm so sorry!
-What is it?

15:01.693 --> 15:03.069
Oh, fuck!

15:03.111 --> 15:06.489
Um, it's my pie.
I put a pie in the oven.

15:06.531 --> 15:08.241
Oh, shit!

15:08.283 --> 15:10.618
Oh, I must have forgotten
to set the timer.

15:10.660 --> 15:12.328
Damn it!

15:12.370 --> 15:14.831
Darn it!
No, no, no, no, Oh, no.

15:14.873 --> 15:16.499
I can get a pie from the store.

15:16.541 --> 15:20.086
No! I wanted to bake you
a pumpkin pie.

15:20.128 --> 15:21.796
It's a Halloween tradition.

15:21.838 --> 15:23.506
-(alarm stops)
-(sighs)

15:23.548 --> 15:25.508
(groans)

15:27.135 --> 15:28.511
-Are you...
-I got to go.

15:28.553 --> 15:30.096
-I'm late for work.
-(sighs): Okay.

15:30.138 --> 15:32.057
But do you have your costume
for the party?

15:32.098 --> 15:34.100
I told you,
I don't want to go alone.

15:34.142 --> 15:35.935
So I'm not going.

15:35.977 --> 15:37.771
(sighs)

15:37.812 --> 15:39.356
Oh.

15:40.899 --> 15:43.276
RADIO ANNOUNCER:
WURG 94.9.

15:43.318 --> 15:47.280
Giving you the Urge,
with Willie the Kid.

15:47.322 --> 15:49.324
Haddonfield's home for rock.

15:49.366 --> 15:51.701
WILLIE THE KID: It is
four days until Halloween.

15:51.743 --> 15:53.745
-Can you believe it?
-(horn honks)

15:53.787 --> 15:56.456
It's time to lock your doors,
grab your knife for the fight.

15:56.498 --> 15:57.999
You ready? You ready in case

15:58.041 --> 16:00.126
the Boogeyman decides
to come out and play?

16:00.168 --> 16:01.670
(over radio):
I know I am.

16:01.711 --> 16:03.755
But let's talk about that
Michael Myers for a minute.

16:03.797 --> 16:06.424
How does one man get shot at,
stabbed up

16:06.466 --> 16:09.260
and then he fall
down the street and get back up

16:09.302 --> 16:12.180
to scare the piss out of
everybody in Haddonfield?

16:12.222 --> 16:14.808
Let me tell you how--
'cause this isn't a man.

16:14.849 --> 16:18.687
This is more than a man.
This is a beast. (growls)

16:18.728 --> 16:20.522
One that doesn't bleed...

16:20.563 --> 16:23.483
I'm pretty sure
that was in the change order.

16:23.525 --> 16:25.735
Hold-hold on a second, Shannon.

16:25.777 --> 16:27.570
Hey, Corey, you're late!

16:27.612 --> 16:29.531
You're late again!

16:29.572 --> 16:31.574
WILLIE THE KID (over radio):
It's been four years.

16:31.616 --> 16:32.534
Where y'all at?

16:32.575 --> 16:34.494
Training for the big day,
perhaps?

16:34.536 --> 16:36.579
Getting yourself in the spirit?

16:36.621 --> 16:38.623
This Boogeyman been sitting
in hibernation,

16:38.665 --> 16:41.126
but trust me, y'all,
he'll be back.

16:42.544 --> 16:45.046
I'm Willie the Kid,
and I'll be creeping it real

16:45.088 --> 16:46.381
on 94.9 WUR...

16:46.423 --> 16:48.383
Corey, you got a second?

16:54.055 --> 16:56.099
What do you think?

16:57.183 --> 16:58.768
Yeah.

16:58.810 --> 17:00.353
Get it registered.

17:00.395 --> 17:02.272
Get some new plates.

17:02.313 --> 17:05.358
-I got no use for it no more.
-Are you serious?

17:05.400 --> 17:07.527
With a good engine pushing you,
finally make it

17:07.569 --> 17:09.696
to work on time,
you know what I mean?

17:09.738 --> 17:11.197
Does it work?

17:11.239 --> 17:14.325
Yeah, it works,
just kind of shitty.

17:18.913 --> 17:20.957
Hey, uh, Ronald?

17:20.999 --> 17:23.126
Thanks.

17:23.168 --> 17:24.878
No problem, kid.

17:24.919 --> 17:27.922
(metallic rattling)

17:27.964 --> 17:30.091
(siren whooping)

17:36.264 --> 17:38.266
(engine shuts off)

17:43.938 --> 17:45.774
You're under arrest.

17:45.815 --> 17:47.859
For being the prettiest girl
I know.

17:47.901 --> 17:49.194
That's nice, Doug.

17:49.235 --> 17:51.571
Is that why you pulled me over?

17:51.613 --> 17:54.074
No. I pulled you over
'cause I miss you.

17:54.115 --> 17:55.533
You miss me?

17:55.575 --> 17:57.077
(chuckling):
Just kidding.

17:57.118 --> 17:58.328
Pulled you over
'cause it looks like

17:58.370 --> 17:59.746
your muffler's about
to fall off.

17:59.788 --> 18:01.247
Better get that fixed
before you have a bigger

18:01.289 --> 18:03.541
-problem on your hands.
-(engine starts)

18:04.918 --> 18:07.629
-(vehicle departing)
-(metallic rattling resumes)

18:07.671 --> 18:11.466
* Oilliphéist in the sea *

18:11.508 --> 18:16.304
* Nail my hands to the door *

18:16.346 --> 18:19.140
* And my knees to the floor *

