31:10.704 --> 31:12.914
(lively chatter, laughter)

31:16.751 --> 31:20.547
* I'm not attractive today,
I'm not a sight for sore eyes *

31:20.588 --> 31:23.383
* I'm not an Adam or Eve, I'm
just a nervous young thing... *

31:23.425 --> 31:25.844
-DEB: There you are!
-Hi.

31:25.885 --> 31:28.722
I thought I missed you.

31:28.763 --> 31:30.181
Who's under the mask?

31:30.223 --> 31:32.809
COREY:
Uh... I'm a scarecrow.

31:32.851 --> 31:34.144
DEB:
What?

31:34.185 --> 31:36.396
-COREY: I said I'm a scarecrow.
-(laughs)

31:36.438 --> 31:39.274
Are you supposed to be scary?

31:39.315 --> 31:40.233
(laughs)

31:40.275 --> 31:41.317
I'll be right there.

31:41.359 --> 31:42.944
I'll be right back, okay?

31:42.986 --> 31:44.738
I'm gonna get us a drink.

31:44.779 --> 31:47.073
* It took a while,
but I learned *

31:47.115 --> 31:49.242
* It took a twist,
but I turned *

31:49.284 --> 31:51.077
* And now it's clear
that I'm blind... *

31:51.119 --> 31:53.121
MAN:
Watch it!

31:53.913 --> 31:56.041
Hey, scarecrow.

31:56.082 --> 31:57.667
See anything you like?

31:57.709 --> 31:59.377
(man laughing)

31:59.419 --> 32:01.004
ALLYSON:
Hey, Lindsay.

32:01.046 --> 32:02.672
-Two vodka sodas.
-Two vodka sodas.

32:02.714 --> 32:05.008
DEB: Lindsay, guess who
Allyson's scarecrow is.

32:05.050 --> 32:07.218
The guy that fucked the
old lady at the nursing home.

32:07.260 --> 32:09.929
Deb, drop it.

32:09.971 --> 32:11.097
DEB:
I'm kidding.

32:11.139 --> 32:13.099
It's actually Corey Cunningham,

32:13.141 --> 32:14.768
the guy that killed that kid.

32:14.809 --> 32:16.353
Don't listen to her, Allyson.

32:16.394 --> 32:19.314
You can be with
whoever you want to be with.

32:20.106 --> 32:21.066
Yeah.

32:21.107 --> 32:22.776
And right now,

32:22.817 --> 32:24.486
I'm with him.

32:28.239 --> 32:30.867
* Bust it,
build it for a year *

32:30.909 --> 32:35.038
* Here's my license,
that's my right. *

32:39.751 --> 32:41.461
(song ends)

32:41.503 --> 32:42.587
(sighs)

32:42.629 --> 32:44.756
("Halloween"
by Dead Kennedys playing)

32:44.798 --> 32:46.633
(crowd cheering)

32:47.634 --> 32:49.469
(Allyson laughs)

32:52.847 --> 32:55.100
(Allyson whoops)

32:57.185 --> 32:59.396
* *

33:00.230 --> 33:02.315
(Allyson grunting rhythmically)

33:04.150 --> 33:05.652
(camera clicking)

33:05.694 --> 33:07.696
(Corey laughing)

33:12.951 --> 33:15.912
* So it's Halloween *

33:15.954 --> 33:18.081
* And you feel like dancing *

33:18.123 --> 33:21.126
* And you feel like shining *

33:21.167 --> 33:23.253
* And you feel like
letting loose *

33:23.294 --> 33:26.214
* Well, what you gonna be? *

33:26.256 --> 33:28.800
* Babe, you better know *

33:28.842 --> 33:31.344
* And you better plan *

33:31.386 --> 33:34.014
* Better plan all day... *

33:34.055 --> 33:35.515
Yeah!

33:35.557 --> 33:38.393
* Better plan all month,
better plan all year... *

33:41.855 --> 33:42.814
(shouts)

33:42.856 --> 33:44.691
(song fades)

33:44.733 --> 33:46.609
* *

33:51.239 --> 33:53.283
(both laughing)

33:57.120 --> 33:58.288
(song resumes)

33:58.329 --> 34:00.040
* It's the only time all year *

34:00.081 --> 34:02.375
* You'll ever admit that *

34:02.417 --> 34:05.128
* I can see your eyes,
I can see your brain *

34:05.170 --> 34:07.505
* Baby, nothing's changed *

34:07.547 --> 34:10.175
* I can see your eyes,
I can see your brain *

34:10.216 --> 34:12.177
* Baby, nothing's changed... *

34:12.218 --> 34:14.721
Hey, man. Can I get a beer?

34:18.433 --> 34:19.809
Hey.

34:22.562 --> 34:25.398
You're just here dancing
and having a good time?

34:27.192 --> 34:28.693
I'm sorry.

34:28.735 --> 34:30.111
You're sorry? Oh.

34:30.153 --> 34:33.281
Sorry?
Sorry for killing my son?

34:35.241 --> 34:37.452
I wake up every day,

34:37.494 --> 34:39.621
and I can't get past the pain.

34:39.662 --> 34:42.916
It kills me. Do you understand?

34:42.957 --> 34:44.417
You think you can come here--

34:44.459 --> 34:46.252
No, you don't understand
if you think you can come here

34:46.294 --> 34:47.629
and take off your little mask

34:47.671 --> 34:49.631
and have a good time
with your friends.

34:49.673 --> 34:52.425
A judge might have said you're
innocent, but I know you.

34:52.467 --> 34:54.094
I know it was no accident.

34:54.135 --> 34:55.428
It was no accident!

34:55.470 --> 34:58.556
You pushed my little boy
because you got mad,

34:58.598 --> 35:01.434
and you lost your fucking mind!

35:01.476 --> 35:04.145
Innocent people don't do that!
No!

35:06.106 --> 35:07.649
Evil people do.

35:07.691 --> 35:09.067
Evil.

35:09.109 --> 35:11.111
* Why not every day? *

35:11.152 --> 35:12.278
* Are you so afraid... *

35:12.320 --> 35:14.447
Corey!

35:15.323 --> 35:17.575
Corey, watch out! Corey!

35:19.744 --> 35:20.995
Corey!

35:21.037 --> 35:22.455
-Stop. Talk to me.
-Why'd you take me in there?

35:22.497 --> 35:24.207
It's why I don't go out.

35:24.249 --> 35:26.334
-What?
-You just, you...

35:26.376 --> 35:28.169
you threw me in the middle
of it, and then you...

35:28.211 --> 35:30.463
-I... I...
-Where were you?

35:30.505 --> 35:32.757
I didn't know
what was happening in there.

35:32.799 --> 35:35.218
I-I was just trying, I was just
trying to help you to just...

35:35.260 --> 35:36.386
I'm not your fucking project,
Allyson!

35:36.428 --> 35:39.264
I just-- Corey, I know!

35:39.305 --> 35:42.475
Okay?
I know what it's like to have

35:42.517 --> 35:44.477
everybody looking at you,
thinking that they know you,

35:44.519 --> 35:46.271
thinking that they know
what you've been through,

35:46.312 --> 35:47.605
but they don't.

35:49.024 --> 35:52.944
But when I look at you--
when I saw you the other day,

35:52.986 --> 35:54.487
I just saw a person.

35:54.529 --> 35:57.949
Just a person just trying
to figure it the fuck out.

35:57.991 --> 36:01.327
Trying to wake up every day
not scared and alone.

36:01.369 --> 36:05.415
But the difference, Allyson,
between me and you

36:05.457 --> 36:07.917
is that people look at me like,

36:07.959 --> 36:10.253
"Who is this guy?
Who is this monster?"

36:10.295 --> 36:13.423
And they look at you like--
They see you like a survivor.

36:13.465 --> 36:14.841
What are you talking about?

36:14.883 --> 36:17.594
I get it.
You survived Michael Myers.

36:17.635 --> 36:20.180
You're a hero with
your struggles, and ask anyone.

36:20.221 --> 36:22.974
I'm the psycho babysitter.
I'm the fucking kid killer.

36:24.017 --> 36:27.604
And you think you can fix me,
but you can't.

36:28.772 --> 36:30.857
I'll spare you the heartache.

36:31.858 --> 36:33.610
(whimpering softly)

36:36.237 --> 36:38.490
* *

36:50.585 --> 36:53.421
-(horn honks)
-BILLY (singsongy): Corey!

36:54.214 --> 36:55.882
(tires screech)

36:55.924 --> 36:57.884
Hey, cool kid. What's up?

36:57.926 --> 36:59.511
Where you going?

36:59.552 --> 37:01.930
There you are, man.
I've been looking for you.

37:01.971 --> 37:04.391
-MARGO: Terry.
-I want to apologize, okay?

37:04.432 --> 37:05.725
MARGO (whispers):
Ugh, Jesus Christ.

37:05.767 --> 37:07.769
TERRY:
So what do you say, Corey? Huh?

37:07.811 --> 37:10.939
How about this?
Handshakes and friendship.

37:13.775 --> 37:16.027
Don't leave him hanging, dude.

37:18.780 --> 37:20.782
* *

37:21.533 --> 37:23.368
-(grunts)
-(Stacy laughing)

37:23.410 --> 37:24.953
What is your problem
with this kid?

37:27.288 --> 37:29.082
-TERRY: This guy fucked up
the LeBaron. -STACY: Hell yeah.

37:29.124 --> 37:31.126
-BILLY: Dollar store designer
frames? -(Corey grunts)

37:31.167 --> 37:33.044
STACY:
Oops. (chuckles)

37:33.086 --> 37:34.796
BILLY: Hey, let me
help you up. Come on.

37:35.505 --> 37:37.298
-(grunts)
-(laughter)

37:37.340 --> 37:38.758
-Sorry.
-Are you okay?

37:38.800 --> 37:40.218
-TERRY: Whoa. Whoa.
-COREY: Get the fuck back!

37:40.260 --> 37:41.428
-Hey! Hey!
-Get back!

37:41.469 --> 37:42.762
-Get back!
-Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

37:42.804 --> 37:44.514
-MARGO: I'm just trying to help.
-Get back!

37:44.556 --> 37:46.307
You gonna murder us?
Same way you killed that kid?

37:47.017 --> 37:48.351
You little psycho bitch.

37:48.393 --> 37:49.936
You don't know
what you're talking about!

37:49.978 --> 37:51.813
-You don't know what you're
talking about. -(chuckles)

37:51.855 --> 37:53.440
You just act like
a goddamn asshole

37:53.481 --> 37:54.941
because your father
treats you like one.

37:54.983 --> 37:55.984
(Stacy laughing)

37:56.026 --> 37:57.944
It's contagious, right?

37:57.986 --> 37:59.195
MARGO:
Shit.

37:59.237 --> 38:00.780
-What did you just say to me?
-That's right.

38:00.822 --> 38:02.782
I know what it looks like
when somebody hates you.

38:02.824 --> 38:04.909
And your father
fucking hates you.

38:04.951 --> 38:07.245
-Hmm? He hates me?
-(grunting)

38:07.287 --> 38:08.621
-MARGO: Billy.
-He hates me, huh?

38:08.663 --> 38:09.706
-He hates me, right?
-Hey!

38:09.748 --> 38:11.624
Billy, knock it off. Billy!

38:11.666 --> 38:13.001
-(Stacy laughing)
-He hates me?

38:13.043 --> 38:14.753
-MARGO: Terry, what the fuck?!
-(Corey screams)

38:14.794 --> 38:16.921
-BILLY: Oh, shit!
-(Corey grunts, body thuds)

38:17.714 --> 38:19.007
-STACY: Oh, shit.
-MARGO: Oh, my God.

38:19.049 --> 38:20.842
-Oh, shit.
-Terry, what did you do?!

38:20.884 --> 38:23.136
-He fell.
-Little dick busted it.

38:23.178 --> 38:24.971
-MARGO: Is he dead?
-STACY: Go down and look.

38:25.013 --> 38:27.140
-No, you go down and look.
-What the fuck?

38:27.182 --> 38:29.517
I didn't push nobody. He fell.

38:29.559 --> 38:30.602
-Bullshit.
-He fell?

38:30.643 --> 38:32.145
Yeah, that's my story.

38:32.187 --> 38:34.147
Let's get out of here.

38:34.189 --> 38:36.441
STACY: Who's the psycho now,
Terry? Who's the psycho?

38:36.483 --> 38:37.650
BILLY:
Little prick deserved it.

38:37.692 --> 38:38.985
TERRY:
Get in the car, Margo.

38:39.027 --> 38:40.278
MARGO (crying):
We killed a kid, man.

38:40.320 --> 38:41.988
BILLY:
Come on.

38:42.030 --> 38:43.156
(car door closes)

38:43.198 --> 38:45.658
(car drives off)

38:45.700 --> 38:49.496
MAN (quietly):
* There's a hole in the boat *

38:49.537 --> 38:51.706
* And it won't stay afloat *

38:54.542 --> 38:56.544
* Oilliphéist in the sea *

38:56.586 --> 38:58.838
(body dragging)

39:00.006 --> 39:03.551
* Nail my hands to the door *

39:03.593 --> 39:05.887
* And my knees to the floor *

39:07.347 --> 39:11.559
* To stop the water
till we reach the shore. *

39:13.311 --> 39:15.188
(loud banging)

39:15.230 --> 39:16.856
Hey, what's happening?

39:16.898 --> 39:18.108
ALLYSON: Just-- I can't get
this fucking thing to turn on.

39:18.149 --> 39:19.776
LAURIE:
Okay, okay. Take a breath.

39:19.818 --> 39:20.694
-Okay, take a deep breath.
-Just let me be mad!

39:20.735 --> 39:22.696
Why can't I be mad?!

39:22.737 --> 39:24.447
-You can.
-(sighs)

39:24.489 --> 39:26.032
You can be mad.

39:26.074 --> 39:27.742
-You can be very, very mad,
-(microwave beeping)

39:27.784 --> 39:29.369
and you can smash things.

39:29.411 --> 39:31.371
Just be careful.
It's addictive.

39:31.413 --> 39:33.623
(microwave whirring)

39:42.674 --> 39:44.300
ALLYSON:
You were right.

39:44.342 --> 39:45.593
I liked him.

39:45.635 --> 39:47.387
LAURIE:
Yeah.

39:47.429 --> 39:48.888
(food pops)

39:48.930 --> 39:52.517
(squeaking)

39:54.477 --> 39:56.604
(breathing heavily)

39:56.646 --> 39:58.898
* *

40:03.278 --> 40:05.697
(soft, shuddering breaths)

40:18.126 --> 40:20.128
* *

40:30.638 --> 40:32.891
(water dripping)

40:38.313 --> 40:40.523
(gasping)

40:44.235 --> 40:45.987
(thudding)

40:47.072 --> 40:49.699
(yelping, gasping)

40:49.741 --> 40:51.451
(breathing heavily)

40:51.493 --> 40:53.703
(choking)

41:06.508 --> 41:09.010
* *

41:18.269 --> 41:20.563
* *

41:22.273 --> 41:24.192
(screams)

41:35.203 --> 41:37.288
(grunting, gasping)

41:57.892 --> 42:00.103
(slow, heavy breathing)

42:03.565 --> 42:05.817
-You see that man in there?
-(gasps)

42:06.651 --> 42:09.738
He take people in there
now and then.

42:10.989 --> 42:13.742
Why'd he let you live?

42:14.534 --> 42:15.994
I say you go back.

42:16.036 --> 42:19.205
You go back in there,
and you get me that mask.

42:19.247 --> 42:21.499
I'm Michael Myers.

42:22.083 --> 42:23.960
-The fuck?
-(laughing)

42:24.961 --> 42:27.589
He not done with you,
you little fuck.

42:27.630 --> 42:29.299
(grunting)

42:29.341 --> 42:31.259
(knife squishes)

42:31.301 --> 42:33.720
(whimpering)

42:34.554 --> 42:35.930
-(knife squishes)
-(grunts)

42:36.765 --> 42:38.725
-(knife squishes)
-(grunts)

42:40.143 --> 42:42.270
(grunts, gasps)

42:42.312 --> 42:44.356
(panting)

42:53.406 --> 42:54.532
(grunts)

42:54.574 --> 42:56.284
(panting)

42:57.452 --> 42:59.704
* *

43:01.706 --> 43:03.416
(dog barking in distance)

43:03.458 --> 43:04.668
JOAN:
Hey!

43:04.709 --> 43:06.961
Where have you been?

43:08.004 --> 43:10.131
I have been worried sick!

43:11.257 --> 43:14.094
Corey, I almost called
the missing persons.

43:14.135 --> 43:15.970
-What is going on with you?
-(banging at door)

43:16.012 --> 43:18.306
Corey, I'm talking to you.

43:19.307 --> 43:21.142
She's no good, damn it.

43:21.184 --> 43:22.727
Open the door.

43:22.769 --> 43:25.689
-Open the door!
-(banging at door)

43:25.730 --> 43:28.108
Are you trying to kill me?

43:29.150 --> 43:31.444
Corey? Corey?

43:31.486 --> 43:33.738
(faucet running)

43:38.493 --> 43:40.161
(glass squeaks)

43:40.954 --> 43:43.123
(breathing heavily)

43:43.164 --> 43:45.166
* *

43:47.961 --> 43:49.671
DEB: No hard feelings
about the promotion, right?

43:49.713 --> 43:51.131
Course not. You deserve it.

43:51.172 --> 43:53.008
(chuckles)
I thought for sure Dr. Mathis

43:53.049 --> 43:54.968
was gonna make you
the charge nurse.

43:55.010 --> 43:57.762
Deb, can I speak to you
a minute?

44:03.101 --> 44:05.145
Okay, Deb, I'm gonna
tell you once...

44:05.186 --> 44:07.939
-(door closes)
-(indistinct conversation)

44:13.987 --> 44:15.739
LAURIE:
People create their own stories

44:15.780 --> 44:17.824
and make their own choices.

44:18.616 --> 44:21.619
They believe
what they want to believe.

44:21.661 --> 44:24.164
I'm hopeful, with perspective,

44:24.205 --> 44:27.208
that my experience
will help others heal.

44:27.250 --> 44:29.294
(engine revs)

44:29.336 --> 44:32.797
You have to ask yourself,
"Am I in control,

44:32.839 --> 44:35.342
"or do the elements control me?

44:35.383 --> 44:37.093
"Life or death.

44:37.135 --> 44:41.431
Suicide or cherry blossoms."

44:42.223 --> 44:44.476
(motorcycle engine
buzzing outside)

44:55.487 --> 44:57.739
* *

45:14.881 --> 45:16.091
-Hi.
-(gasps)

45:16.132 --> 45:17.509
Sorry, I didn't mean
to scare you.

45:17.550 --> 45:19.135
I'm just waiting for Allyson.

45:21.096 --> 45:22.472
ALLYSON:
Corey?

45:26.351 --> 45:28.269
Everything okay?

45:29.062 --> 45:32.607
Uh, I got jumped
on the way home last night.

45:32.649 --> 45:34.859
These guys...

45:37.904 --> 45:41.241
Those kids from the gas station
that were messing with me--

45:41.282 --> 45:44.285
I tried to stand up for myself,
and they, um...

45:46.413 --> 45:48.289
Oh, I'm sorry.

45:51.835 --> 45:53.962
I just came 'cause
I wanted to talk to you.

45:54.004 --> 45:56.214
I wanted to say that I'm sorry
and there's...

45:56.256 --> 45:57.465
no excuse.

45:57.507 --> 45:59.592
But if you could, please,
if you could just

45:59.634 --> 46:01.678
take a walk with me.

46:01.720 --> 46:03.805
Please?

46:14.691 --> 46:16.943
* *

46:22.741 --> 46:24.993
I killed someone.

46:34.961 --> 46:37.172
* *

46:51.561 --> 46:53.605
(clattering)

47:07.869 --> 47:10.121
(notes play flatly)

47:12.040 --> 47:14.000
We were making paper planes,

47:14.042 --> 47:16.836
but he wanted to watch
a monster movie.

47:16.878 --> 47:18.963
* *

47:19.005 --> 47:21.633
Everything happened so fast.

47:26.012 --> 47:28.390
I just wanted it
to be a fun night.

47:30.350 --> 47:33.937
That's all, just...
a good night.

47:39.234 --> 47:41.444
And then it all went bad.

47:45.073 --> 47:47.617
ALLYSON:
I heard what happened.

47:47.659 --> 47:51.246
I know it sounds crazy,
but when...

47:51.287 --> 47:54.958
people would talk about it,
it was like I knew you.

47:55.000 --> 47:58.336
Like I was looking for you.

47:58.378 --> 48:00.588
And then she brought you to me.

48:03.925 --> 48:06.136
(high-pitched whistling)

48:07.762 --> 48:10.015
Has he done something bad?

48:10.056 --> 48:11.474
I don't understand
why you're here.

48:11.516 --> 48:14.269
No, no. He's seeing
my granddaughter.

48:14.310 --> 48:16.062
I introduced them, actually.

48:16.104 --> 48:17.897
Your granddaughter
should be so lucky

48:17.939 --> 48:19.733
as to be with a boy like Corey.

48:19.774 --> 48:22.027
He's handsome. He's sensitive.

48:22.068 --> 48:24.070
(sighs) I don't like it
when he stays out

48:24.112 --> 48:26.948
all night with girls,
but he's grown.

48:26.990 --> 48:29.284
He can do what he wants.

48:30.827 --> 48:33.079
Yes.

48:36.041 --> 48:38.585
I know he's had
his difficulties.

48:39.586 --> 48:40.795
My son.

48:40.837 --> 48:42.213
This town turned against him

48:42.255 --> 48:43.923
after the accident
with Jeremy Allen.

48:43.965 --> 48:45.342
They would've felt for him.

48:45.383 --> 48:46.718
They would've helped him heal.

48:46.760 --> 48:49.596
But because your boogeyman
disappeared,

48:49.637 --> 48:51.639
they needed a new one.

48:55.810 --> 48:57.645
I'm sorry.

49:00.190 --> 49:01.691
ALLYSON: After my mom
and dad were killed,

49:01.733 --> 49:03.943
I just wanted
to burn it all to the ground

49:03.985 --> 49:06.446
-and get away from Haddonfield.
-Why not leave?

49:06.488 --> 49:08.114
Why stay?

49:08.156 --> 49:10.617
All my memories are here.

49:12.452 --> 49:14.162
I think both your parents
got killed

49:14.204 --> 49:15.955
and your grandma
feels guilty about it,

49:15.997 --> 49:17.415
so she's making you her child.

49:17.457 --> 49:19.626
If you could've seen her
before therapy,

49:19.668 --> 49:21.628
sobering up, and me...

49:21.670 --> 49:23.380
I'm just terrified to think
what would happen

49:23.421 --> 49:25.131
if she were all alone
if I left.

49:25.173 --> 49:27.050
So, what, you got to stay here,
protect her

49:27.092 --> 49:28.635
from herself forever?

49:32.013 --> 49:33.598
Look...

49:33.640 --> 49:36.017
I'm sorry I lost my head
at the party

49:36.059 --> 49:38.144
and I walked away.

49:38.186 --> 49:40.105
That was a mistake.

49:41.690 --> 49:43.525
When I look at you, I...

49:45.527 --> 49:48.154
I know I can tell you
the truth.

49:48.196 --> 49:50.323
I'm not afraid of these people.

49:50.365 --> 49:52.492
I'm not afraid anymore.

49:52.534 --> 49:55.662
You tell me that you want
to burn it down,

49:55.704 --> 49:57.580
or you tell me you want
to burn it to the ground.

49:57.622 --> 50:00.834
(chuckling):
Hey. Twice in one week.

50:00.875 --> 50:03.503
Pretty cool. Hot diggity.

50:03.545 --> 50:05.005
Hey, you said you, uh...
you were gonna call.

50:05.046 --> 50:06.923
You were... you were gonna call,
but you didn't call.

50:06.965 --> 50:09.092
No, I owe you a call.

50:09.134 --> 50:11.302
Did I... did I do
something wrong or...

50:11.344 --> 50:12.721
I'm with someone.

50:12.762 --> 50:14.389
Oh. Oh.

50:14.431 --> 50:16.391
Oops. Uh, sorry for that.

50:16.433 --> 50:17.976
I'm sorry for the intrusion.

50:18.018 --> 50:20.270
Well, um, you know, it's, uh...
it's Joe Grillo's, uh...

50:20.311 --> 50:21.980
Hey, Joe! Hey.

50:22.022 --> 50:23.690
Joe Grillo's birthday today.

50:23.732 --> 50:25.608
And Joe Ross, uh,
he made a sponge cake.

50:25.650 --> 50:27.736
You two want to stop by,
get a slice

50:27.777 --> 50:30.113
-after whatever you guys
are doing? -We're good.

50:30.155 --> 50:31.948
Oh. Okay, you're good.

50:31.990 --> 50:33.241
Let me tell you, it's, uh...

50:33.283 --> 50:34.868
If you change your mind,
there's...

50:34.909 --> 50:36.536
She said we're good!

50:40.623 --> 50:43.168
(sniffs)
Hey, buddy, you got a problem?

50:43.960 --> 50:46.087
We're good.

50:47.756 --> 50:49.549
Oh, shit.

50:49.591 --> 50:51.426
Allyson.

50:51.468 --> 50:54.929
So you call
Mr. Aggravated Manslaughter

50:54.971 --> 50:56.806
at night when you can't sleep?

50:56.848 --> 50:58.266
Hmm?

50:58.308 --> 51:01.311
When you see the Boogeyman
in your nightmares?

51:01.353 --> 51:03.646
You feel safe with this guy?

51:04.647 --> 51:06.524
(quiet murmuring)

51:10.028 --> 51:12.280
(trembling breaths)

51:16.493 --> 51:18.203
OFFICER MULANEY:
Hey, man.

51:18.244 --> 51:20.705
Messing around.

51:20.747 --> 51:22.457
Allyson.

51:23.291 --> 51:25.085
Nah, nah, nah.

51:25.126 --> 51:26.586
-Psycho.
-OFFICER: You good, Mulaney?

51:26.628 --> 51:28.421
It's all good. It's all good.

51:28.463 --> 51:30.298
We need to go kick
somebody's ass?

51:30.340 --> 51:32.717
No, no. I got this.

51:37.806 --> 51:40.308
ALLYSON:
Just burn it all to the ground.

51:41.309 --> 51:43.103
I'll light the match.

51:43.144 --> 51:46.189
("Come 2 Me" by Johnny Goth
playing)

51:46.231 --> 51:48.858
* Come sit by my side *

51:49.651 --> 51:52.696
* You've got a sad look
in your eye *

51:52.737 --> 51:57.659
* Don't let them
pull you in tonight *

51:58.493 --> 52:01.413
* Oh, no *

52:02.163 --> 52:04.499
* I don't want *

52:06.292 --> 52:10.630
* To see you *

52:10.672 --> 52:12.799
* Alone *

52:16.928 --> 52:18.680
Do you want to come in?

52:18.722 --> 52:21.891
* If you fly too close,
you might die *

52:21.933 --> 52:23.226
Another night.

52:23.268 --> 52:26.271
* Like a moth to my light *

52:26.312 --> 52:31.401
* Don't let those flames
get you high *

52:31.443 --> 52:34.904
* Oh, no. *

52:34.946 --> 52:36.990
-(song stops)
-(car engine idling)

52:37.032 --> 52:39.284
(motorcycle engine revving)

52:41.494 --> 52:43.705
(song resumes)

53:00.138 --> 53:02.390
* *

53:08.146 --> 53:10.357
(song ends)

53:28.583 --> 53:30.835
(traffic rumbling above)

53:45.975 --> 53:48.436
(crickets chirping)

54:06.663 --> 54:08.581
(flashlight clicks off)

54:17.048 --> 54:18.842
(flashlight clicks on)

54:18.883 --> 54:20.301
Ah, fuck!

54:20.343 --> 54:22.804
(panting)

54:24.055 --> 54:25.432
(muffled grunting)

54:25.473 --> 54:28.059
* *

54:30.395 --> 54:31.938
(Corey grunts)

54:31.980 --> 54:33.356
(panting)

54:33.398 --> 54:35.316
(Corey laughing)

54:38.653 --> 54:40.989
(Corey continues laughing)

54:42.407 --> 54:44.242
OFFICER MULANEY:
Hey!

54:44.284 --> 54:46.661
You don't fuck
with Doug Mulaney!

54:54.002 --> 54:56.004
(panting)

54:59.049 --> 55:00.800
(screeching)

55:04.429 --> 55:06.723
Where are you? Huh?

55:07.515 --> 55:10.060
You say it was an accident.

55:11.353 --> 55:13.063
But I know what you did.

55:15.523 --> 55:18.651
(rocks clattering)

55:18.693 --> 55:21.571
I'm gonna fuck your face up,
you little shit.

55:31.873 --> 55:33.500
The fuck is that?

55:43.093 --> 55:45.011
(chuckles softly)

55:47.097 --> 55:49.349
(groans, grunts)

55:49.391 --> 55:51.726
-(breathing heavily)
-(grunting)

55:58.400 --> 56:00.860
(groaning)

56:01.778 --> 56:03.571
COREY:
Help.

56:03.613 --> 56:06.032
Show me how to do it.

56:07.242 --> 56:09.327
Get up, get up, get up.

56:09.369 --> 56:11.037
Get up!

56:11.079 --> 56:13.123
* *

56:26.594 --> 56:29.597
(grunting)

56:35.937 --> 56:37.605
(yells)

56:48.283 --> 56:49.659
(grunts)

56:55.957 --> 56:58.209
(heavy breathing continues)

57:06.384 --> 57:09.596
(grunting, gasping)

57:19.022 --> 57:21.608
* *

57:23.109 --> 57:25.153
(wheezing softly)

57:31.576 --> 57:34.829
-(knocking at door)
-(dog barks in distance)

57:36.414 --> 57:38.083
Who is it?

57:38.124 --> 57:40.001
COREY:
It's me.

57:40.794 --> 57:42.587
Oh, my God. Are you okay?

57:42.629 --> 57:44.839
I don't know
what's happening to me.

57:49.469 --> 57:51.137
What's going on?

57:51.179 --> 57:53.223
(Corey breathing heavily)

57:55.350 --> 57:57.060
Look at me.

57:58.645 --> 58:00.855
(continues breathing heavily)

58:02.399 --> 58:04.317
Who did this to you?

58:04.359 --> 58:06.111
Hey.

58:07.195 --> 58:08.655
Look at me.

58:08.697 --> 58:11.116
Did Michael Myers let you live?

58:11.157 --> 58:13.034
Or did you escape?

58:16.413 --> 58:18.665
(trembling breaths)

58:23.044 --> 58:24.963
Does it hurt?

58:25.964 --> 58:28.717
No. No.

58:31.219 --> 58:33.638
My mother saved me.

58:48.445 --> 58:50.697
(heavy breathing)

59:02.292 --> 59:04.252
(birds chirping)

59:04.294 --> 59:06.338
* *

59:22.729 --> 59:24.898
DEB:
You're fucking him, aren't you?

59:24.939 --> 59:27.901
It's, like, the perfect story
of Haddonfield in a way.

59:27.942 --> 59:29.903
Cute young girl falls
for local creep.

59:29.944 --> 59:31.279
Imagine if your grandmother had

59:31.321 --> 59:33.281
fallen in love
with Michael Myers.

59:33.323 --> 59:34.866
But she didn't.
I heard she stabbed him

59:34.908 --> 59:36.409
in the neck with
a fucking knitting needle.

59:36.451 --> 59:37.744
ALLYSON:
What's your problem, Deb?

59:37.786 --> 59:39.204
You talk to me
like I'm not even here.

59:39.245 --> 59:41.623
Do you ever just shut
your goddamn mouth?

59:42.415 --> 59:43.750
(chuckles) I know, right?

59:43.792 --> 59:45.418
I know I talk too much.

59:45.460 --> 59:48.630
I just get so excited about
all that Boogeyman bullshit.

59:48.672 --> 59:52.092
Uh-uh. No.
I-I'm vetoing that trade.

59:52.133 --> 59:54.594
Your second receiver
for Mark's last-place defense

59:54.636 --> 59:56.096
reeks of collusion.

59:56.137 --> 59:58.515
It's not a straight-up swap.

59:58.556 --> 1:00:00.517
You want to win
the championship with class?

1:00:00.558 --> 1:00:01.976
Stop cheating.

1:00:02.769 --> 1:00:04.854
Stop cheating.

1:00:05.438 --> 1:00:07.732
I keep seeing his eyes.

1:00:07.774 --> 1:00:09.609
Are we talking about Michael
or this kid?

1:00:09.651 --> 1:00:12.696
Michael's eyes in Corey.

1:00:12.737 --> 1:00:16.658
Lindsay, I was so sure.

1:00:18.368 --> 1:00:19.869
Just like the first time.

1:00:19.911 --> 1:00:21.663
Hey, Roger.

1:00:23.289 --> 1:00:25.917
There's someone
I want you to meet.

1:00:26.960 --> 1:00:28.628
MR. ALLEN:
I always liked Corey.

1:00:28.670 --> 1:00:31.297
You know, some kids, you can
tell they're a pain in the ass,

1:00:31.339 --> 1:00:33.008
but Corey was a good kid.

1:00:33.049 --> 1:00:35.093
And I just couldn't imagine
he'd be capable

1:00:35.135 --> 1:00:37.345
of hurting anyone on purpose.

1:00:37.387 --> 1:00:38.847
But with the trial, I...

1:00:38.888 --> 1:00:42.434
just started spinning
with theories, and...

1:00:42.475 --> 1:00:43.852
and eventually I thought,

1:00:43.893 --> 1:00:45.311
"Give it up.
You're never gonna get closure.

1:00:45.353 --> 1:00:46.896
There's no such thing."

1:00:46.938 --> 1:00:49.983
A couple of years go by, and
I'd see him every now and then,

1:00:50.025 --> 1:00:51.901
see the way people avoided him

1:00:51.943 --> 1:00:54.279
or how they made faces
behind his back,

1:00:54.320 --> 1:00:56.489
which, if I'm honest,
pissed me off.

1:00:56.531 --> 1:00:59.743
Because I felt like
they took my pain...

1:01:01.202 --> 1:01:03.955
...my despair,

1:01:03.997 --> 1:01:05.999
and they made it about them.

1:01:07.500 --> 1:01:09.711
And then, yesterday,
I'm on my way to work.

1:01:09.753 --> 1:01:11.212
There he is.

1:01:11.254 --> 1:01:14.674
And I think,
"I'm gonna say something,

1:01:14.716 --> 1:01:16.092
"prove my wife wrong.

1:01:16.134 --> 1:01:19.471
Let's find a way
to forgive this kid."

1:01:19.512 --> 1:01:24.601
And I pull up next to him,
and he looks at me,

1:01:24.642 --> 1:01:27.062
and it's not him.

1:01:27.896 --> 1:01:30.190
At least not in the eyes.

1:01:30.231 --> 1:01:33.902
And I don't know, man.

1:01:33.943 --> 1:01:37.030
The hairs on the back
of my neck stood up.

1:01:39.240 --> 1:01:42.535
Right then, I felt like
I got my answer.

1:01:43.703 --> 1:01:46.748
The kid who used to mow
our lawn didn't kill my son.

1:01:46.790 --> 1:01:48.416
I know that.

1:01:49.250 --> 1:01:51.753
But the guy I saw
on the side of the road

1:01:51.795 --> 1:01:54.464
was down a dark path.

1:01:54.506 --> 1:01:57.926
Did the town do this to him
after the accident?

1:01:57.967 --> 1:02:00.261
Or was it always there?

1:02:05.392 --> 1:02:07.060
DR. MATHIS: You're just
laughing at all my jokes,

1:02:07.102 --> 1:02:09.646
-aren't you?
-(Deb laughs)

1:02:09.688 --> 1:02:11.731
(sighs):
Oh, my God.

1:02:11.773 --> 1:02:14.067
All right, Alexa.

1:02:14.109 --> 1:02:17.237
Play "Tell Me With Your Eyes"
by Rob Galbraith.

1:02:17.278 --> 1:02:18.697
ALEXA: Here's
"Tell Me With Your Eyes..."

1:02:18.738 --> 1:02:21.574
This house is so...

1:02:21.616 --> 1:02:22.867
rich.

1:02:22.909 --> 1:02:24.077
-(Dr. Mathis sighs)
-(music begins)

1:02:24.119 --> 1:02:26.746
(fingers snapping)

1:02:26.788 --> 1:02:30.583
Baby, I have been waiting
all day for this.

1:02:30.625 --> 1:02:34.337
I've been saving this bottle
of Au Bon Climat.

1:02:34.379 --> 1:02:36.965
You looked so fucking hot
at the office today.

1:02:37.007 --> 1:02:39.467
-Hmm.
-(sighs)

1:02:39.509 --> 1:02:40.635
Mind if I...

1:02:40.677 --> 1:02:42.470
Bedroom's down the hall.

1:02:42.512 --> 1:02:44.055
Clean up. Take a shower.

1:02:44.097 --> 1:02:46.516
In fact,
I'll meet you in there.

1:02:46.558 --> 1:02:48.476
(both laugh)

1:02:49.477 --> 1:02:50.562
Yes, yes.

1:02:50.603 --> 1:02:52.647
* And you wanna love me *

1:02:52.689 --> 1:02:53.773
* Say you wanna love me... *

1:02:53.815 --> 1:02:55.316
Mm-hmm.

1:02:56.317 --> 1:02:57.318
Yes.

1:02:57.360 --> 1:03:00.405
(music continues in distance)

1:03:00.447 --> 1:03:03.908
* I don't care about
your social place *

1:03:03.950 --> 1:03:07.787
* All you need is
a look on your face *

1:03:07.829 --> 1:03:10.290
* When you wanna love me,
yeah *

1:03:10.331 --> 1:03:12.292
* Say you wanna love me *

1:03:12.334 --> 1:03:14.753
* If you wanna love me *

1:03:14.794 --> 1:03:16.338
* Say you wanna love me *

1:03:16.379 --> 1:03:21.176
* Why don't you tell me
with your eyes *

1:03:21.217 --> 1:03:23.303
* If you wanna love me *

1:03:23.345 --> 1:03:24.971
* Say you wanna love me... *

1:03:25.013 --> 1:03:27.057
Holy shit. (clicks tongue)

1:03:27.098 --> 1:03:29.184
Is there a doctor in the house?

1:03:29.225 --> 1:03:33.813
* If you wanna one time,
one time with me, mama *

1:03:33.855 --> 1:03:35.190
Yeah, baby. All right.

1:03:35.231 --> 1:03:36.858
Got the cheese.
We got the crackers.

1:03:36.900 --> 1:03:38.068
We're ready.

1:03:38.109 --> 1:03:39.361
(knob creaks)

1:03:40.987 --> 1:03:43.323
-(thump)
-(Dr. Mathis grunts)

1:03:43.365 --> 1:03:45.033
Dr. Mathis?

1:03:47.869 --> 1:03:49.454
-(thumping)
-(music stops)

1:03:49.496 --> 1:03:50.914
Dr. Mathis?

1:03:53.166 --> 1:03:55.502
-(knob creaks)
-(water stops)

1:03:55.543 --> 1:03:57.253
Dr. Mathis?

1:04:08.598 --> 1:04:10.558
(crickets chirping)

1:04:10.600 --> 1:04:12.310
Dr. Mathis?

1:04:30.829 --> 1:04:32.706
(grunting)

1:04:32.747 --> 1:04:34.624
* *

1:04:34.666 --> 1:04:36.167
(grunting, choking)

1:04:38.378 --> 1:04:40.213
(screams)

1:04:41.339 --> 1:04:44.718
(whimpering, screaming)

1:04:44.759 --> 1:04:47.387
(Corey grunting, groaning)

1:04:48.179 --> 1:04:50.348
-(lock clicks)
-(grunting angrily)

1:04:54.602 --> 1:04:58.064
Please, please, please, please.
Please, please, please, please.

1:04:58.106 --> 1:05:00.650
(angry grunting
and pounding continue)

1:05:05.530 --> 1:05:06.865
WOMAN (over phone):
911...

1:05:06.906 --> 1:05:08.700
* *

1:05:10.952 --> 1:05:13.455
(screams)

1:05:14.164 --> 1:05:16.624
(breathing heavily)

1:05:17.959 --> 1:05:20.086
(choking)

1:05:28.803 --> 1:05:30.305
(choking)

1:05:39.814 --> 1:05:41.191
(screams)

1:05:44.527 --> 1:05:46.988
* *

1:06:04.756 --> 1:06:08.009
("Burn It Down"
by Boy Harsher playing)

1:06:09.094 --> 1:06:11.721
* Take my heart *

1:06:14.099 --> 1:06:16.685
* Pull me down *

1:06:19.354 --> 1:06:22.023
* Take my heart *

1:06:24.401 --> 1:06:27.487
* And burn it down *

1:06:27.529 --> 1:06:29.572
* *

1:06:46.715 --> 1:06:48.466
COREY:
After the accident,

1:06:48.508 --> 1:06:51.594
I'd ride my bike over here
and I'd sit up on this roof.

1:06:53.596 --> 1:06:56.182
And I'd look up at that tower.

1:06:56.224 --> 1:06:58.226
Wonder if I could climb
to the top.

1:06:59.811 --> 1:07:01.521
It was summoning me.

1:07:01.563 --> 1:07:05.775
Like a watchtower or beacon
calling me to live my old life.

1:07:05.817 --> 1:07:07.068
To be happy again.

1:07:07.110 --> 1:07:10.196
* Burn it down *

1:07:10.947 --> 1:07:13.742
I have something like that, too.

1:07:14.534 --> 1:07:17.579
It always gave me hope,
you know, things would--

1:07:17.620 --> 1:07:19.497
well, maybe somehow
things would go back

1:07:19.539 --> 1:07:21.666
to the way they used to be.

1:07:23.793 --> 1:07:25.754
Before everything changed.

1:07:25.795 --> 1:07:28.965
* Burn it down. *

1:07:29.007 --> 1:07:31.092
Infected.

1:07:31.885 --> 1:07:35.180
I got to get away from
everybody who knows me.

1:07:37.098 --> 1:07:38.725
But I don't, I...

1:07:39.934 --> 1:07:41.811
I don't want to go alone.

1:07:48.276 --> 1:07:50.153
Corey, come on.

1:07:50.195 --> 1:07:51.863
-(chuckles)
-Stop.

1:07:51.905 --> 1:07:54.157
I think you're scared that
you don't have enough bandages

1:07:54.199 --> 1:07:55.992
to keep me together.

1:07:56.034 --> 1:07:57.118
Corey, what are you...?!

1:07:57.160 --> 1:07:58.787
(feet thud)

1:08:01.331 --> 1:08:04.209
-(laughing)
-Are you okay?

1:08:04.250 --> 1:08:05.543
What, are you insane?

1:08:05.585 --> 1:08:07.379
What, are you trying
to kill yourself?

1:08:07.420 --> 1:08:09.464
I'm not interested
in immortality.

1:08:12.008 --> 1:08:13.093
-(grunts)
-(song ends)

1:08:13.134 --> 1:08:14.427
(groans)

1:08:14.469 --> 1:08:17.055
(dogs barking in distance)

1:08:17.097 --> 1:08:19.432
The hell is going on out here?

1:08:19.474 --> 1:08:21.393
Yo, this is private property.

1:08:21.434 --> 1:08:23.895
Not safe to be doing
whatever the hell you do...

1:08:24.854 --> 1:08:27.232
Corey Cunningham.

1:08:27.273 --> 1:08:28.775
What you doing out here,
you ugly motherfucker?

1:08:28.817 --> 1:08:31.069
-ALLYSON: Corey, stop it.
-You gonna scare all the kids.

1:08:31.111 --> 1:08:32.445
You stop.

1:08:34.364 --> 1:08:36.324
I don't know
who the fuck you talking to,

1:08:36.366 --> 1:08:39.828
but, uh, I know who you are.

1:08:40.662 --> 1:08:42.789
Yeah, I know
the Laurie Strode story.

1:08:42.831 --> 1:08:47.168
She teased a man with brain
damage, and then he snapped.

1:08:47.210 --> 1:08:48.712
Look at you.

1:08:48.753 --> 1:08:50.797
You gonna make a little name
for yourself now, huh?

1:08:50.839 --> 1:08:53.091
Walking around with
this dumb bitch right here.

1:08:53.133 --> 1:08:54.300
ALLYSON:
You never shut up.

1:08:54.342 --> 1:08:55.427
Hear his voice everywhere.

1:08:55.468 --> 1:08:57.429
Oh, you're goddamn right you do.

1:08:57.470 --> 1:08:58.972
And once Willie
get in your ear,

1:08:59.014 --> 1:09:02.642
it's like your favorite song
stuck in your head.

1:09:02.684 --> 1:09:04.352
(chuckles)

1:09:06.271 --> 1:09:08.231
Y'all get the hell
up off my property

1:09:08.273 --> 1:09:09.691
before I fuck y'all up.

1:09:10.692 --> 1:09:12.277
(door opens)

1:09:12.318 --> 1:09:14.154
-All right.
-(door closes)

1:09:14.195 --> 1:09:16.656
You're right.

1:09:16.698 --> 1:09:19.284
Let's do it.

1:09:19.325 --> 1:09:21.995
I don't want to be
in Haddonfield anymore.

1:09:22.037 --> 1:09:23.997
I want to be with you.

1:09:24.039 --> 1:09:26.291
* *

1:09:40.930 --> 1:09:43.600
JOAN:
(sniffs) I can smell her on you.

1:09:43.641 --> 1:09:46.311
She's trying to take you
away from me, isn't she?

1:09:46.353 --> 1:09:48.021
That's where you go
every night.

1:09:48.063 --> 1:09:50.774
Well, I say go.

1:09:52.192 --> 1:09:54.903
You go right now!

1:09:54.944 --> 1:09:56.988
Get out of my house!

1:09:59.908 --> 1:10:01.785
Oh, no. No.

1:10:11.419 --> 1:10:13.421
I hope you find love.

1:10:17.092 --> 1:10:19.344
(slow, rhythmic knocking)

1:10:21.930 --> 1:10:24.349
(slow, rhythmic knocking
continues)

1:10:27.352 --> 1:10:29.604
(slow, rhythmic knocking
continues)

1:10:34.359 --> 1:10:36.361
Allyson?

1:10:37.946 --> 1:10:40.365
(slow, rhythmic knocking
continues)

1:10:43.576 --> 1:10:45.954
LAURIE:
It's nice to see you.

1:10:55.296 --> 1:10:57.757
You know,
there are two kinds of evil.

1:10:59.676 --> 1:11:02.595
There's the evil that exists
as an external force

1:11:02.637 --> 1:11:05.473
that threatens the well-being
of the tribe.

1:11:06.307 --> 1:11:10.979
Survival depends on
understanding and awareness

1:11:11.021 --> 1:11:15.567
and fear of physical threat
to our daily lives.

1:11:15.608 --> 1:11:18.653
The other kind of evil
lives inside us.

1:11:18.695 --> 1:11:23.491
Like a sickness or an infection.

1:11:25.076 --> 1:11:29.539
It's more dangerous because
we may not know we're infected.

1:11:31.291 --> 1:11:33.501
(slow, rhythmic knocking
continues)

1:11:36.212 --> 1:11:37.922
Am I a bad person?

1:11:37.964 --> 1:11:39.966
(laughs)

1:11:40.008 --> 1:11:41.926
Are you?

1:11:41.968 --> 1:11:43.511
Well...

1:11:45.221 --> 1:11:47.474
...we're both fucked-up.

1:11:48.975 --> 1:11:51.853
-I want to help you, Corey.
-(chuckles)

1:11:51.895 --> 1:11:53.146
Let me help you.

1:11:53.188 --> 1:11:55.315
Or let me find help for you.

1:11:55.357 --> 1:11:56.858
You can't have her.

1:11:56.900 --> 1:11:59.819
Allyson is not equipped
for this relationship,

1:11:59.861 --> 1:12:02.113
and I will not
let her get hurt.

1:12:02.155 --> 1:12:04.074
So stay the fuck away...

1:12:04.115 --> 1:12:05.950
You started this!

1:12:05.992 --> 1:12:08.870
You brought me in!
You invited me!

1:12:10.246 --> 1:12:13.375
But you're the one to blame.

1:12:15.085 --> 1:12:17.879
"You want to do it,
or you want me to?"

1:12:17.921 --> 1:12:19.964
* *

1:12:24.260 --> 1:12:26.388
If I can't have her...

1:12:27.681 --> 1:12:29.891
...no one will.

1:12:31.935 --> 1:12:35.480
You want to help Allyson?
Let her live her life.

1:12:38.066 --> 1:12:40.568
She has me now.

1:12:47.492 --> 1:12:49.494
You should give in.

1:12:51.246 --> 1:12:53.540
You should surrender
to that feeling you had

1:12:53.581 --> 1:12:56.084
the first time
you ever looked into his eyes.

1:13:00.630 --> 1:13:03.633
You secretly hope
Michael comes back for you.

1:13:06.261 --> 1:13:09.139
(chuckles)

1:13:09.180 --> 1:13:11.099
I'm the psycho.

1:13:12.183 --> 1:13:14.436
You're the freak show.

1:13:15.186 --> 1:13:17.063
* *

1:13:40.128 --> 1:13:42.130
(notes play flatly)

1:13:51.431 --> 1:13:52.640
What's wrong?

1:13:52.682 --> 1:13:53.767
COREY (over phone):
We need to leave.

1:13:53.808 --> 1:13:56.603
I can't right now. I'm working.

1:13:56.644 --> 1:13:58.772
COREY:
Tonight, then.

1:13:58.813 --> 1:14:02.609
Will you meet me at 9:00?

1:14:02.650 --> 1:14:04.903
At the diner off 74.

1:14:04.944 --> 1:14:07.155
We need to talk about
your grandmother.

1:14:08.656 --> 1:14:11.117
She wants to kill me.

1:14:11.159 --> 1:14:13.078
-What?
-Yeah.

1:14:13.119 --> 1:14:15.121
I can't take it anymore.

1:14:15.163 --> 1:14:17.916
It's time to say goodbye
to Haddonfield.

1:14:20.293 --> 1:14:23.046
(Corey panting)

1:14:24.506 --> 1:14:26.800
You got something I need.

1:14:28.468 --> 1:14:30.679
(both grunting)

1:14:47.696 --> 1:14:50.490
(Corey shouts, groans)

1:14:50.532 --> 1:14:53.868
You're just a man
in a Halloween mask.

1:14:53.910 --> 1:14:55.662
What are you gonna do now?

1:14:55.704 --> 1:14:58.331
(both breathing heavily)

1:14:58.373 --> 1:15:00.583
* *

1:15:09.884 --> 1:15:12.095
(breathing heavily)

1:15:13.179 --> 1:15:15.807
-(playful chatter)
-(crickets chirping)

1:15:19.019 --> 1:15:20.603
-(entry bell chimes)
-BILLY: Call him after.

1:15:20.645 --> 1:15:21.896
I don't want
to go to your house, man.

1:15:21.938 --> 1:15:23.273
Your dad always
fucking yells at us.

1:15:23.314 --> 1:15:24.733
Too fucking bad.
You should've got your own.

1:15:24.774 --> 1:15:26.359
Shouldn't have
any of these anyway.

1:15:26.401 --> 1:15:28.028
Why can't we go to her house?
She's the one that's rich.

1:15:28.069 --> 1:15:29.195
-Oh, what? Yeah. Shoot.
-TERRY: What the fuck?

1:15:29.237 --> 1:15:31.031
What?

1:15:31.072 --> 1:15:32.282
(engine revving)

1:15:34.242 --> 1:15:36.119
He's dead! Get in!

1:15:36.161 --> 1:15:37.579
Oh, shit. Shit.

1:15:52.093 --> 1:15:54.262
Did you find
what you're looking for?

1:15:54.304 --> 1:15:56.598
I imagine you're going
on a wonderful trip.

1:15:58.266 --> 1:16:00.477
-Were you gonna tell me?
-What difference does it make?

1:16:00.518 --> 1:16:01.895
It makes a big difference,
Allyson.

1:16:01.936 --> 1:16:04.731
I feel he is capable
of real harm.

1:16:04.773 --> 1:16:06.983
Is that what bothers you?

1:16:07.025 --> 1:16:10.904
Is it suspicion or paranoia?

1:16:10.945 --> 1:16:12.906
Intuition? An inkling?

1:16:12.947 --> 1:16:14.157
You got an inkling?

1:16:14.199 --> 1:16:16.618
I went to his home.
I met his mother.

1:16:16.659 --> 1:16:18.912
I know. He told me.

1:16:19.954 --> 1:16:21.581
So, you're what?
You're stalking him now?

1:16:21.623 --> 1:16:23.166
-No.
-And you're threatening him.

1:16:23.208 --> 1:16:25.627
-What did you say to him?
-I-I see the same thing in him

1:16:25.669 --> 1:16:27.921
-that I saw in Michael.
-Michael.

1:16:27.962 --> 1:16:29.673
Michael Myers is who you are.

1:16:29.714 --> 1:16:31.549
You're not listening to me,
Allyson.

1:16:31.591 --> 1:16:32.926
I am trying to protect you.

1:16:32.967 --> 1:16:34.427
I don't want your protection!

1:16:34.469 --> 1:16:38.556
But you-you can have
a good life, Allyson.

1:16:38.598 --> 1:16:39.891
A good life.

1:16:39.933 --> 1:16:41.685
Just not with him.

1:16:42.477 --> 1:16:44.771
You pretend like you moved on,
but it's bullshit.

1:16:44.813 --> 1:16:46.481
You're actually just obsessed
with death,

1:16:46.523 --> 1:16:47.899
like it's some sort of game.

1:16:47.941 --> 1:16:49.609
And you're not gonna rest
until you've finished it

1:16:49.651 --> 1:16:52.237
or until everybody else is as
fucking miserable as you are!

1:16:52.278 --> 1:16:54.948
I need to get out of here
before this town kills

1:16:54.989 --> 1:16:57.826
the one person that actually
makes me feel something.

1:16:59.160 --> 1:17:01.955
-He is on a dark path!
-(sighs)

1:17:01.996 --> 1:17:03.623
I'm not gonna
let this happen to you!

1:17:03.665 --> 1:17:05.166
You have to believe me!

1:17:05.208 --> 1:17:07.919
Believe you?

1:17:07.961 --> 1:17:09.963
You want me to believe you?

1:17:10.005 --> 1:17:13.091
Because of the hysteria
that you caused

1:17:13.133 --> 1:17:16.761
when I trusted you,
my friends are dead.

1:17:16.803 --> 1:17:18.304
My parents are dead.

1:17:18.346 --> 1:17:22.267
You're the one
that's capable of fucking harm!

1:17:22.308 --> 1:17:24.728
(gunfire and tires screeching
over headphones)

1:17:27.647 --> 1:17:29.149
(cat meows)

1:17:31.317 --> 1:17:33.236
(crickets chirping)

1:17:35.030 --> 1:17:36.406
BILLY: You sure
he turned in here, dude?

1:17:36.448 --> 1:17:38.033
TERRY: Yeah, it's like
his hideout or something.

1:17:38.074 --> 1:17:39.492
It's where he works.

1:17:39.534 --> 1:17:42.120
-His work is a dump.
-It actually is a dump.

1:17:42.162 --> 1:17:43.955
STACY: (chuckles) Okay, no,
but seriously, where is he?

1:17:43.997 --> 1:17:45.290
-TERRY: There's the bike.
-Shit, dude, pull over.

1:17:45.331 --> 1:17:47.917
STACY:
This is gonna be so crazy.

1:17:48.877 --> 1:17:50.837
-Let's go.
-MARGO: Billy, can you hurry up?

1:17:50.879 --> 1:17:52.464
-Corey!
-You're squishing me.

1:17:52.505 --> 1:17:54.174
-God.
-Where'd he go?

1:17:54.215 --> 1:17:55.383
Come out, Corey!

1:17:57.260 --> 1:17:59.262
Corey, I just want to kiss
and make up, my man!

1:17:59.304 --> 1:18:00.930
-Come on!
-Stop being a punk!

1:18:00.972 --> 1:18:02.849
-(singsongy): Corey!
-Where you at, man?

1:18:02.891 --> 1:18:05.101
I'll show you what happens when
you mess with my dad's car!

1:18:05.143 --> 1:18:06.978
-(laughs)
-Can we hurry this up, man?

1:18:10.065 --> 1:18:11.524
Oh, I got an idea.

1:18:11.566 --> 1:18:14.152
Billy, back the car up.

1:18:14.194 --> 1:18:15.111
Bet.

1:18:15.153 --> 1:18:16.529
Grab that chain. Let's go.

1:18:16.571 --> 1:18:19.366
MARGO: Terry, there's somebody
in the office.

1:18:19.407 --> 1:18:20.867
Stop being a chickenshit.

1:18:20.909 --> 1:18:22.452
Run it through the wheel.
All right?

1:18:22.494 --> 1:18:24.454
We're gonna tie it
to the back of the car,

1:18:24.496 --> 1:18:26.498
and then we'll drag it
till there's nothing left.

1:18:27.499 --> 1:18:29.084
Dusty-ass bike.

1:18:30.085 --> 1:18:32.003
-(laughs)
-Shit.

1:18:32.045 --> 1:18:34.756
-Let's go, Billy. Billy!
-Come on, Terry. Hurry up, man.

1:18:34.798 --> 1:18:36.758
-Someone's here.
-Billy!

1:18:38.134 --> 1:18:41.096
Come on, Billy!
Let's get this punk!

1:18:41.137 --> 1:18:42.055
Let's go!

1:18:42.097 --> 1:18:43.723
Oh, my God. Billy.

1:18:43.765 --> 1:18:46.226
Billy, what are you trying
to do, man? Suck your own...

1:18:46.267 --> 1:18:47.811
Oh, my God!

1:18:47.852 --> 1:18:48.978
What the fuck?!

1:18:49.020 --> 1:18:50.855
MARGO:
Terry?

1:18:50.897 --> 1:18:52.774
What's wrong?

1:18:52.816 --> 1:18:54.109
Billy's dead!

1:18:54.150 --> 1:18:55.527
-What?
-MARGO: What?!

1:18:55.568 --> 1:18:56.986
-What are you talking about?!
-(engine starts)

1:18:57.028 --> 1:18:59.739
-(engine revs)
-Oh, shit.

1:18:59.781 --> 1:19:02.450
-(Stacy panting)
-Stacy? Stacy?

1:19:02.492 --> 1:19:04.577
(screams)
What... what's happening?!

1:19:04.619 --> 1:19:05.912
(engine revving)

1:19:05.954 --> 1:19:08.498
* *

1:19:11.459 --> 1:19:12.419
(yells) Damn it!

1:19:12.460 --> 1:19:14.921
(panting)

1:19:14.963 --> 1:19:16.756
-MARGO: Stacy!
-(grunting)

1:19:16.798 --> 1:19:18.341
(whimpering, panting)

1:19:26.641 --> 1:19:28.226
(screams)

1:19:30.812 --> 1:19:32.814
(gunfire continues
over headphones)

1:19:41.656 --> 1:19:42.949
Help, help, help, help!

1:19:42.991 --> 1:19:45.952
Help! You got to help me!
Help me!

1:19:45.994 --> 1:19:47.871
STACY:
Margo!

1:19:47.912 --> 1:19:49.247
Oh, my God!

1:19:49.289 --> 1:19:52.000
-Margo! Margo!
-(Margo whimpering)

1:19:52.042 --> 1:19:53.585
Speak to me.

1:19:53.626 --> 1:19:56.254
Are you okay? Are you okay?

1:19:57.589 --> 1:19:59.799
Stay calm.
I'm gonna get you out of here.

1:19:59.841 --> 1:20:01.343
Don't worry.
I'm gonna get you out.

1:20:01.384 --> 1:20:03.011
-(Margo crying)
-Try to be calm.

1:20:03.053 --> 1:20:04.929
(gasps, screams)

1:20:04.971 --> 1:20:07.307
It's loaded.

1:20:07.349 --> 1:20:09.184
Stay here.

1:20:11.311 --> 1:20:13.355
* *

1:20:24.407 --> 1:20:25.950
(Margo crying)

1:20:25.992 --> 1:20:27.494
MARGO:
I don't want to die.

1:20:27.535 --> 1:20:29.954
-Help me! Help me!
-RONALD: Hey, hey!

1:20:29.996 --> 1:20:31.956
Hold on. Hold on. Hold still.

1:20:31.998 --> 1:20:33.750
Hold still!
I'll get it off you.

1:20:33.792 --> 1:20:36.878
(screams) There he is!

1:20:38.296 --> 1:20:39.547
Corey?

1:20:40.340 --> 1:20:41.883
TERRY:
I got you!

1:20:43.385 --> 1:20:45.512
-I got you, you fucking psycho!
-RONALD: No, don't!

1:20:45.553 --> 1:20:47.681
(gunshot)

1:20:47.722 --> 1:20:49.933
(Margo crying)

1:20:54.187 --> 1:20:56.356
Stacy. Stacy.

1:20:56.398 --> 1:20:58.066
God.

1:20:58.817 --> 1:21:00.110
Oh, my God.

1:21:01.903 --> 1:21:03.321
-MARGO: Terry.
-Margo!

1:21:03.363 --> 1:21:04.447
Terry.

1:21:04.489 --> 1:21:06.741
-(crying)
-God. Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

1:21:06.783 --> 1:21:08.034
Where's Stacy?

1:21:08.076 --> 1:21:10.245
TERRY:
Stacy's dead.

1:21:11.413 --> 1:21:12.831
You're dead, too.

1:21:12.872 --> 1:21:14.708
-What? (gasps)
-Terry!

1:21:14.749 --> 1:21:16.126
(grunts)

1:21:16.167 --> 1:21:18.420
-(knobs creaking)
-(gas hissing)

1:21:22.924 --> 1:21:25.176
(screaming, gurgling)

1:21:30.849 --> 1:21:33.393
MARGO (crying):
No.

1:21:34.436 --> 1:21:35.562
Oh, shit.

1:21:38.982 --> 1:21:41.234
* *

1:21:45.822 --> 1:21:48.116
WOMAN (on TV):
It's the zest of a lemon peel.

1:21:48.158 --> 1:21:50.118
Gives a little fresh twist.

1:21:50.160 --> 1:21:52.328
So the blueberries, obviously,
are really hot.

1:21:52.370 --> 1:21:53.830
And then when it's
all ready to go,

1:21:53.872 --> 1:21:55.749
we'll go and freeze the custard
and then whip...

1:21:55.790 --> 1:21:57.250
Ronald?

1:21:58.001 --> 1:21:59.294
Ronald?

1:21:59.336 --> 1:22:01.046
(slow, heavy breathing)

1:22:01.087 --> 1:22:03.131
I have laundry.

1:22:05.300 --> 1:22:06.926
I can put it in your dresser,

1:22:06.968 --> 1:22:08.636
or I can leave it
in this basket here.

1:22:08.678 --> 1:22:10.597
(on TV): ...this container
and put it in the freezer

1:22:10.638 --> 1:22:12.640
for about, oh,
half an hour to an hour

1:22:12.682 --> 1:22:13.975
so it'll firm up.

1:22:14.017 --> 1:22:15.477
Now we're gonna eat it.

1:22:15.518 --> 1:22:17.270
That looks good.

1:22:17.312 --> 1:22:19.064
A little ice cream,
a little cookie...

1:22:19.105 --> 1:22:20.607
(screams)

1:22:20.648 --> 1:22:23.777
Ooh, the hotline is open,
and we are taking requests.

1:22:23.818 --> 1:22:26.071
Songs for the resurrection.

1:22:26.112 --> 1:22:28.114
What's gonna get
our monster out?

1:22:28.156 --> 1:22:29.824
Give us something
to scream about?

1:22:29.866 --> 1:22:31.159
(chuckles)

1:22:31.201 --> 1:22:32.452
Caller, you're on the air.

1:22:32.494 --> 1:22:34.204
WOMAN (on phone):
Willie, you should be

1:22:34.245 --> 1:22:36.414
ashamed of yourself
exploiting these tragedies.

1:22:36.456 --> 1:22:39.709
There are three missing people
right now in Haddonfield.

1:22:39.751 --> 1:22:42.587
"Beware," sir,
"that when fighting monsters,

1:22:42.629 --> 1:22:45.090
"you yourself do not
become a monster,

1:22:45.131 --> 1:22:47.801
"for when you gaze long
into the abyss,

1:22:47.842 --> 1:22:50.261
the abyss gazes also into you."

1:22:51.471 --> 1:22:54.265
Nietzsche also said,
"Without music..."

1:22:54.307 --> 1:22:56.184
(button clicks)

1:22:56.226 --> 1:22:58.395
"...life would be a mistake."

1:22:58.436 --> 1:23:02.023
("I Was a Teenage Werewolf"
by The Cramps playing)

1:23:06.319 --> 1:23:09.030
(slow, heavy breathing)

1:23:12.826 --> 1:23:14.828
Can I help you?

1:23:14.869 --> 1:23:17.288
("I Was a Teenage Werewolf"
continues)

1:23:19.165 --> 1:23:23.086
-* I was a teenage werewolf *
-(muffled screaming)

1:23:24.004 --> 1:23:27.924
* Braces on my fangs *

1:23:27.966 --> 1:23:31.052
* I was a teenage werewolf... *

1:23:31.094 --> 1:23:32.929
Hey, man, who the hell are you?

1:23:32.971 --> 1:23:34.389
Hey, what the f... Oh!

1:23:34.431 --> 1:23:37.350
(grunting, gasping)

1:23:39.728 --> 1:23:42.564
(grunts, groans)

1:23:45.150 --> 1:23:46.276
(screaming)

1:23:46.317 --> 1:23:48.361
(record scratches)

1:23:49.988 --> 1:23:52.073
* A Midwest monster... *

1:23:52.115 --> 1:23:55.076
(record skipping, scratching)

1:24:05.253 --> 1:24:08.423
(song continues over radio,
record skipping and scratching)

1:24:13.178 --> 1:24:15.638
(music stops)

1:24:15.680 --> 1:24:17.932
(engine shuts off)

1:24:17.974 --> 1:24:20.101
(entry bell jingles)

1:24:24.522 --> 1:24:26.775
(rock music plays low
in background)

1:24:33.031 --> 1:24:34.783
(entry bell jingles)

1:24:36.368 --> 1:24:38.370
(quiet chatter)

1:24:38.411 --> 1:24:40.246
-(door closes)
-(sighs)

1:24:40.288 --> 1:24:42.499
(cell phone buzzing)

1:24:47.212 --> 1:24:49.881
Allyson, I'm sorry.

1:24:49.923 --> 1:24:52.092
I'm sorry for what I said.

1:24:52.133 --> 1:24:54.511
I'm sorry. Please.

1:24:54.552 --> 1:24:56.763
And I just want you
to come home.

1:24:56.805 --> 1:24:58.848
(knocking at door)

1:25:01.810 --> 1:25:03.853
(crickets chirping)

1:25:20.662 --> 1:25:22.706
* *

1:25:57.365 --> 1:25:59.576
(glass clinking)

1:26:35.862 --> 1:26:38.406
(crickets chirping)

1:27:04.182 --> 1:27:06.267
(sighs softly)

1:27:17.445 --> 1:27:18.780
(line ringing)

1:27:18.822 --> 1:27:20.782
-OPERATOR: 911.
-Yes.

1:27:20.824 --> 1:27:24.119
I would like to report
a suicide.

1:27:24.160 --> 1:27:28.415
1206 Mill's End Road.

1:27:32.627 --> 1:27:34.838
(breathing deeply)

1:27:48.309 --> 1:27:50.562
(deep, trembling breath)

1:27:55.442 --> 1:27:57.652
(shuddering breaths)

1:28:01.531 --> 1:28:03.783
(whimpering)

1:28:10.707 --> 1:28:13.001
(gunshot)

1:28:16.338 --> 1:28:18.548
(door creaking)

1:28:19.591 --> 1:28:21.885
Did you really think
I'd kill myself?

1:28:24.220 --> 1:28:26.514
(body thudding)

1:28:29.559 --> 1:28:32.687
(wheezing)

1:28:41.696 --> 1:28:44.491
-I have tried so hard...
-(groaning)

1:28:44.532 --> 1:28:48.620
...to have compassion
and find mercy.

1:28:52.415 --> 1:28:54.542
But what's the point?

1:28:54.584 --> 1:28:57.045
(gun clicking)

1:29:03.343 --> 1:29:06.137
You came here to kill me,
so do it.

1:29:16.272 --> 1:29:18.775
(vehicle approaching)

1:29:18.817 --> 1:29:21.069
(engine rattling and clanking)

1:29:25.198 --> 1:29:27.409
(chuckling)

1:29:31.538 --> 1:29:33.164
You know,
we all learn the truth

1:29:33.206 --> 1:29:34.916
about each other eventually.

1:29:38.169 --> 1:29:40.463
Did you really think

1:29:40.505 --> 1:29:44.759
that Allyson
was gonna be with you?

1:29:46.094 --> 1:29:48.096
If I can't have her...

1:29:49.431 --> 1:29:50.557
(gasping)

1:29:50.598 --> 1:29:52.767
LAURIE:
You son of a bitch.

1:29:55.520 --> 1:29:57.772
(door opens)

1:30:03.528 --> 1:30:05.613
(knife clatters on floor)

1:30:06.948 --> 1:30:09.576
* *

1:30:09.617 --> 1:30:11.661
(shuddering breaths)

1:30:11.703 --> 1:30:13.747
What did you do?

1:30:13.788 --> 1:30:15.749
What did you do to him?

1:30:15.790 --> 1:30:17.625
(crying):
No, no.

1:30:18.793 --> 1:30:21.171
(Allyson whimpering)

1:30:22.589 --> 1:30:24.758
No. No.

1:30:26.468 --> 1:30:27.927
(crying):
Why did you do this?

1:30:27.969 --> 1:30:30.513
-No.
-Corey, come back. Come back.

1:30:32.390 --> 1:30:34.476
ALLYSON (trembling):
No, no.

1:30:36.144 --> 1:30:38.563
(screams)

1:30:40.523 --> 1:30:42.150
You!

1:30:43.318 --> 1:30:45.820
(sobbing)

1:30:49.199 --> 1:30:51.242
(panting)

1:31:01.503 --> 1:31:03.755
(panting)

1:31:25.860 --> 1:31:27.320
(gun drops to floor)

1:31:27.362 --> 1:31:29.906
(sobbing)

1:31:31.533 --> 1:31:33.034
(engine starts)

1:31:37.038 --> 1:31:39.082
(wind whistling)

1:31:45.463 --> 1:31:47.882
* *

1:31:49.300 --> 1:31:51.720
(slow, heavy footsteps)

1:31:53.555 --> 1:31:55.765
(gasps)

1:31:58.560 --> 1:32:00.729
* *

1:32:04.065 --> 1:32:06.026
(grunting)

1:32:09.029 --> 1:32:10.572
(choking)

1:32:15.535 --> 1:32:16.911
(neck snaps)

1:32:19.414 --> 1:32:22.167
(slow, heavy breathing)

1:32:32.344 --> 1:32:35.055
(slow, heavy breathing)

1:32:37.349 --> 1:32:39.601
(gasping breaths)

1:32:41.478 --> 1:32:42.937
(brakes squeal)

1:32:46.107 --> 1:32:47.776
(siren wailing in distance)

1:32:47.817 --> 1:32:50.236
(cell phone buzzing)

1:32:52.781 --> 1:32:54.407
FRANK (over phone):
Allyson, where's Laurie?

1:32:54.449 --> 1:32:57.619
We're responding to a call.
She called in a suicide.

1:32:59.662 --> 1:33:02.332
(slow, heavy breathing)

1:33:13.718 --> 1:33:16.971
-(trembling breaths)
-(slow, heavy footsteps)

1:33:20.433 --> 1:33:22.977
(microwave whirring)

1:33:27.649 --> 1:33:29.859
(tapping)

1:33:35.782 --> 1:33:37.701
(blade scrapes)

1:33:38.576 --> 1:33:40.829
(both breathing heavily)

1:33:57.303 --> 1:33:59.389
-(splattering)
-(microwave beeps)

1:33:59.431 --> 1:34:01.850
(grunting)

1:34:03.393 --> 1:34:04.769
(straining)

1:34:06.938 --> 1:34:09.774
(quiet, gasping breaths)

1:34:16.823 --> 1:34:19.284
(choking)

1:34:24.456 --> 1:34:25.540
(yells)

1:34:25.582 --> 1:34:27.834
(coughing)

1:34:29.878 --> 1:34:32.714
(grunting)

1:34:35.383 --> 1:34:38.219
(choking)

1:34:39.554 --> 1:34:41.514
(straining)

1:34:41.556 --> 1:34:43.600
No!

1:34:43.641 --> 1:34:46.019
(straining)

1:34:46.061 --> 1:34:49.022
(garbage disposal whirring)

1:34:51.232 --> 1:34:54.402
(Laurie yelling)

1:35:08.583 --> 1:35:10.960
(yells)

1:35:11.002 --> 1:35:14.089
(pained yelling)

1:35:15.590 --> 1:35:18.259
(screaming)

1:35:20.720 --> 1:35:23.264
(straining)

1:35:36.611 --> 1:35:38.905
(yells)

1:35:45.245 --> 1:35:47.288
(yells)

1:35:47.330 --> 1:35:49.916
(panting heavily)

1:35:51.543 --> 1:35:53.253
(grunts)

1:35:57.465 --> 1:35:59.843
(grunting)

1:36:05.640 --> 1:36:07.475
(straining)

1:36:11.855 --> 1:36:14.024
(both breathing heavily)

1:36:27.996 --> 1:36:31.041
* *

1:36:42.052 --> 1:36:44.471
(grunts fiercely)

1:36:52.020 --> 1:36:54.272
* *

1:37:02.822 --> 1:37:05.033
I've run from you.

1:37:06.159 --> 1:37:08.370
I have chased you.

1:37:10.872 --> 1:37:13.208
I have tried to contain you.

1:37:15.794 --> 1:37:18.380
I have tried to forgive you.

1:37:22.342 --> 1:37:27.305
I thought maybe
you were the Boogeyman.

1:37:27.347 --> 1:37:29.099
No.

1:37:29.140 --> 1:37:33.603
You're just a man
who's about to stop breathing.

1:37:40.985 --> 1:37:42.696
(grunts)

1:37:42.737 --> 1:37:45.448
(weak, gasping breaths)

1:37:45.490 --> 1:37:47.659
(wheezing)

1:37:47.701 --> 1:37:49.911
(panting)

1:37:57.002 --> 1:37:58.545
Do it.

1:37:59.546 --> 1:38:00.880
Do it!

1:38:00.922 --> 1:38:03.299
* *

1:38:07.762 --> 1:38:10.015
(gasping weakly)

1:38:12.934 --> 1:38:13.977
Do it.

1:38:14.019 --> 1:38:16.021
(yells)

1:38:16.062 --> 1:38:18.064
No!

1:38:19.733 --> 1:38:21.651
-(yells)
-(bone snaps)

1:38:23.570 --> 1:38:26.614
I'm not gonna let this
happen to you.

1:38:39.878 --> 1:38:42.130
(gasping weakly)

1:38:48.970 --> 1:38:51.222
LAURIE (whispers):
It's okay.

1:38:53.725 --> 1:38:55.977
* *

1:39:06.529 --> 1:39:08.281
(indistinct
police radio chatter)

1:39:08.323 --> 1:39:10.492
Get out of the way. Stay here.

1:39:10.533 --> 1:39:12.202
Just stay back.

1:39:13.995 --> 1:39:15.663
-(banging on door)
-Laurie!

1:39:25.465 --> 1:39:27.509
* *

1:39:41.981 --> 1:39:43.525
(sighs)

1:39:46.695 --> 1:39:48.446
Michael.

1:39:49.197 --> 1:39:51.324
He's dead.

1:39:53.910 --> 1:39:55.787
Not dead enough.

1:39:56.621 --> 1:39:58.498
MAN:
This isn't how we do it.

1:39:59.290 --> 1:40:01.167
-MAN 2: You're all crazy.
-MAN 3: What are you doing?

1:40:01.209 --> 1:40:02.585
Where are you taking him?

1:40:02.627 --> 1:40:04.754
Time for Haddonfield
to start healing.

1:40:04.796 --> 1:40:07.340
-Let's show them all.
-(siren whooping)

1:40:11.219 --> 1:40:13.263
This is not how it works.

1:40:14.055 --> 1:40:15.849
It is tonight.

1:40:15.890 --> 1:40:17.851
OFFICER (over radio):
Uh, stronger on radio silence.

1:40:17.892 --> 1:40:19.144
That's got to be a command.

1:40:19.185 --> 1:40:20.854
-OFFICER 2: Copy that.
-OFFICER 3: Copy.

1:40:20.895 --> 1:40:23.857
-Let's go.
-(siren whooping)

1:40:23.898 --> 1:40:27.444
* *

1:40:34.117 --> 1:40:36.786
* *

1:40:51.259 --> 1:40:54.095
* *

1:41:17.911 --> 1:41:20.622
* *

1:41:38.640 --> 1:41:40.642
* *

1:41:59.077 --> 1:42:01.329
* *

1:42:20.098 --> 1:42:22.350
* *

1:42:23.435 --> 1:42:25.812
(takes deep breath)

1:42:27.188 --> 1:42:29.399
(takes deep breath)

1:42:44.748 --> 1:42:47.208
(machinery squeaking
and whirring)

1:42:50.712 --> 1:42:52.672
LAURIE:
The body of Michael Myers

1:42:52.714 --> 1:42:55.008
was disposed of
in a midnight procession.

1:42:55.050 --> 1:42:58.261
There would be no tombstone,
no memorial.

1:42:58.303 --> 1:43:00.764
The mysteries were put to bed,

1:43:00.805 --> 1:43:04.476
and the story as we told it
was to fade with time.

1:43:08.646 --> 1:43:11.649
You were right about Corey.

1:43:13.234 --> 1:43:15.779
I know he killed those people.

1:43:20.450 --> 1:43:22.702
He was consumed by evil.

1:43:27.040 --> 1:43:29.709
LAURIE:
The events of Haddonfield

1:43:29.751 --> 1:43:32.545
that created so much violence
and bloodshed

1:43:32.587 --> 1:43:34.964
finally had resolve.

1:43:38.927 --> 1:43:41.221
* *

1:43:41.262 --> 1:43:43.556
REPORTER: Reports now confirm
that Michael Myers

1:43:43.598 --> 1:43:47.268
has indeed been killed dead
after an attempted assault

1:43:47.310 --> 1:43:49.896
of Haddonfield resident
Laurie Strode.

1:43:49.938 --> 1:43:52.899
What an incredible story
of survival

1:43:52.941 --> 1:43:55.193
through decades of disturbances
in our local community.

1:43:55.235 --> 1:43:56.611
Finally...

1:44:02.992 --> 1:44:05.787
LAURIE:
New beginnings lay ahead.

1:44:06.621 --> 1:44:08.748
Fear moves through all of us,

1:44:08.790 --> 1:44:11.459
and we decide
when to surrender.

1:44:12.585 --> 1:44:15.922
I've said goodbye
to my boogeyman,

1:44:15.964 --> 1:44:18.758
but the truth is
evil doesn't die.

1:44:19.634 --> 1:44:21.720
It changes shape.

1:44:26.307 --> 1:44:28.518
(doorbell rings)

1:44:40.530 --> 1:44:43.491
I wanted you to know
I was thinking about you.

1:44:43.533 --> 1:44:45.702
I want to thank you
for what you did.

1:44:48.455 --> 1:44:50.373
Enjoy.

1:45:01.801 --> 1:45:05.513
What was it you were saying
about those cherry blossoms?

1:45:16.816 --> 1:45:18.860
* *

1:45:31.539 --> 1:45:33.792
(birds chirping)

